ours%20in%20thrilling%20draw%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691170207000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102434007%2Cimgsize-73964.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fhockey%2Ftop-stories%2Fasian-champions-trophy-india-and-japan-share-honours-in-thrilling-draw%2Farticleshow%2F102433940.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20and%20Japan%20played%20out%20a%20thrilling%201-1%20draw%20at%20the%20Asian%20Champions%20Trophy%20hockey%20tournament.%20Misfiring%20India%20failed%20to%20capitalise%20despite%20getting%20several%20chances%20to%20win%20against%20a%20resilient%20Japanese%20team.%20India%20won%20their%20tournament%20opener%20against%20China%207-2%20on%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fhockey%2Ftop-stories%2Fasian-champions-trophy-india-and-japan-share-honours-in-thrilling-draw%2Farticleshow%2F102433940.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%5C%22As%20Hot%20As%20A%20Jacuzzi%5C%22%3A%20World's%20Oceans%20Record%20Hottest%20Surface%20Temperature%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20oceans%20set%20a%20new%20temperature%20record%20this%20week%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20knock-on%20effects%20on%20the%20planet's%20climate%2C%20marine%20life%20and%20coastal%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20temperature%20of%20the%20oceans'%20surface%20rose%20to%2020.96%20degrees%20Celsius%20(69.7%20Fahrenheit)%20on%20Friday%2C%20according%20to%20European%20Union%20climate%20observatory%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20record%20was%2020.95C%20in%20March%202016%2C%20a%20spokeswoman%20for%20the%20EU's%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20samples%20tested%20excluded%20polar%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOceans%20have%20absorbed%2090%20percent%20of%20the%20excess%20heat%20produced%20by%20human%20activity%20since%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%20industrial%20age%2C%20according%20to%20scientists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20excess%20heat%20continues%20to%20accumulate%20as%20greenhouse%20gases%20--%20mainly%20from%20burning%20oil%2C%20gas%20and%20coal%20--%20continue%20to%20accumulate%20in%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20the%20average%20ocean%20temperature%20has%20been%20besting%20seasonal%20heat%20records%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%20since%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ocean%20heatwave%20is%20an%20immediate%20threat%20to%20some%20marine%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Piers%20Forster%20of%20the%20International%20Centre%20for%20Climate%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Leeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20already%20seeing%20coral%20bleaching%20in%20Florida%20as%20a%20direct%20result%20and%20I%20expect%20more%20impacts%20will%20surface.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overheating%20of%20the%20oceans%20is%20predicted%20to%20have%20other%20effects%20on%20marine%20plant%20and%20animal%20life%20too%2C%20including%20on%20the%20migration%20of%20certain%20species%20and%20the%20spread%20of%20invasive%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20threaten%20fish%20stocks%20and%20thus%20undermine%20food%20security%20in%20certain%20parts%20of%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWarmer%20oceans%20are%20also%20less%20capable%20of%20absorbing%20carbon%20dioxide%20(CO2)%2C%20reinforcing%20the%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20higher%20temperatures%20are%20likely%20to%20come%2C%20since%20the%20El%20Nino%20phenomenon%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20warm%20waters%20up%2C%20has%20only%20just%20begun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20expect%20the%20worst%20effects%20of%20the%20current%20El%20Nino%20to%20be%20felt%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023%20and%20continue%20into%20subsequent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20bath%20water%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20there%20are%20certainly%20short-term%20factors%2C%20the%20main%20long-term%20cause%20is%20without%20a%20doubt%20the%20accumulation%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20caused%20by%20human%20activity%2C%20primarily%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rowan%20Sutton%2C%20director%20of%20climate%20research%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20figures%20follow%20a%20string%20of%20record%20highs%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20temperatures%20of%2038.3C%20--%20as%20hot%20as%20a%20jacuzzi%20--%20were%20recorded%20off%20the%20Florida%20coast%2C%20which%20could%20be%20a%20world%20record%20high%20for%20a%20point%20measurement%20if%20the%20figure%20is%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20surface%20waters%20of%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20rose%20to%20a%20record-high%20average%20temperature%20of%2024.9C%2C%20according%20to%20provisional%20data%20from%20the%20US%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20(NOAA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20Atlantic%20usually%20only%20reaches%20its%20peak%20temperature%20in%20September%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20March%2C%20the%20month%20when%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20begins%20to%20warm%20up%20after%20winter%2C%20temperatures%20have%20been%20higher%20than%20in%20previous%20years%20and%20the%20gap%20with%20past%20records%20has%20continued%20to%20widen%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%20has%20become%20a%20key%20point%20for%20observing%20the%20heating%20of%20the%20world's%20oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20July%2C%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%20broke%20its%20daily%20heat%20record%2C%20with%20a%20median%20temperature%20of%2028.71C%2C%20according%20to%20Spain's%20leading%20maritime%20research%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarine%20heatwaves%20have%20become%20twice%20as%20frequent%20since%201982%2C%20according%20to%20a%202019%20report%20by%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202100%2C%20they%20could%20be%2010%20times%20more%20intense%20than%20they%20were%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%2020th%20century%20if%20pollutant%20emissions%20are%20not%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20coal%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20debates%20in%20the%20upcoming%20United%20Nations%20climate%20talks%2C%20dubbed%20COP28%2C%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691169840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2Fm6ue63t4_ocean-generic-pixabay-650_625x300_31_July_18.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-hot-as-a-jacuzzi-worlds-oceans-record-hottest-surface-temperature-4270684%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20world's%20oceans%20set%20a%20temperature%20record%20in%20the%20past%20week%2C%20with%20their%20surface%20hitting%2020.96%20degrees%20Celsius%20(69.7%20Fahrenheit)%2C%20European%20Union%20climate%20observatory%20data%20showed%20on%20Friday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-hot-as-a-jacuzzi-worlds-oceans-record-hottest-surface-temperature-4270684%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-hot-as-a-jacuzzi-worlds-oceans-record-hottest-surface-temperature-4270684%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-hot-as-a-jacuzzi-worlds-oceans-record-hottest-surface-temperature-4270684%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Rust%E2%80%99%20Armorer%20Waives%20Evidentiary%20Hearing%2C%20Clearing%20Way%20for%20Manslaughter%20Trial%22%