of%20non-performing%20assets%20(i.e%2C%20loss-making%20NPAs)%20and%20write-offs.%20These%20were%20presented%20through%20an%20article%20on%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20June%2018%2C%20entitled%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-modi-government-must-answer-for-indias-historic-bank-loss-of-rs-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3EThe%20Modi%20Government%20Must%20Answer%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Historic%20Bank%20Loss%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EIt%20covered%20the%20first%20eight%20years%2C%20nine%20months%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20but%20now%20that%20we%20have%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20(RBI)%20figure%20for%20the%20full%20nine%20years%2C%20the%20amount%20lost%20by%20all%20banks%20increases%20from%20Rs%2012%2C09%2C606%20crore%20to%20Rs%2012%2C50%2C553%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENever%20before%20in%20the%20history%20of%20India%20had%20banks%20lost%20and%20wiped%20out%20such%20a%20gigantic%20amount%2C%20year%20after%20year%2C%20without%20a%20whisper%20of%20a%20scam%20or%20any%20public%20debate%20of%20consequence.%20As%20expected%2C%20public%20sector%20banks%20were%20hit%20the%20most%2C%20but%20private%20banks%20also%20picked%20up%20this%20virus%20and%20suffered.%20Retribution%20has%2C%20of%20course%2C%20been%20sharper%20and%20swifter%20in%20private%20banks%20%E2%80%93%20as%20Yes%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fed-arrests-yes-bank-founder-rana-kapoor-under-pmla%5C%22%3ERana%20Kapoor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcbi-registers-fir-in-icici-bank-videocon-loan-case%5C%22%3EChanda%20Kochhar%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20ICICI%20realised%20to%20their%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20third%20article%20of%20the%20series%20(read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fmodi-government-npas-loans-write-off-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3Efirst%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-modi-government-must-answer-for-indias-historic-bank-loss-of-rs-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3Esecond%3C%2Fa%3E%20articles)%2C%20we%20reiterate%20with%20updated%20data%20how%20our%20bank%20deposits%20were%20used%20to%20square%20the%20accounts%20of%20wilful%20defaulters%2C%20asset-strippers%2C%20and%20politically%20blessed%20fraudsters.%20Many%20among%20the%20latter%20who%20rose%20to%20prominence%20with%20(and%20hovered%20around)%20Narendra%20Modi%20looted%20lakhs%20of%20crores%20from%20bank%20funds%20and%20then%20invariably%20scooted%20abroad%20to%20lovely%20pre-paid%20mansions%20and%20to%20other%20luxuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fmodi-government-npas-loans-write-off-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3EHow%20in%20First%20Eight%20Years%20of%20Modi%20Government%2C%20Nearly%20Rs%2012%20Lakh%20Crore%20%E2%80%98Disappeared%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20one%20has%20been%20brought%20back%20to%20face%20trial%20and%20jail%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20while%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%20had%20ensured%20that%20the%20mighty%20Ramalingam%20Raju%20went%20to%20jail%20for%20his%20Satyam%E2%80%99s%20frauds.%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20regime%20was%20booed%20out%20as%20corrupt%20by%20swashbuckling%20TV%20channels%20reporting%20scam%20after%20scam%2C%20which%20were%20revealed%20ever%20so%20dramatically%20by%20a%20rockstar%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG).%20It%20is%20a%20different%20matter%2C%20of%20course%2C%20that%20many%20of%20those%20TV%20channels%20later%20sold%20themselves%20to%20Modi%20or%20his%20capitalist%20buddies%2C%20and%20the%20ex-CAG%20is%20choking%20from%20the%20overfeed%20he%20was%20rewarded%20with%20by%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20pointed%20query%20on%20what%20%E2%80%9Csteps%20(have%20been)%20taken%20to%20recover%20this%20amount%20and%20punishments%20meted%20to%20each%20of%20the%20top%20twenty%20fraudsters%E2%80%9D%2C%20Sitharaman%20replied%2C%20quite%20inanely%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cbanks%20are%20required%20to%20lodge%20complaints%2C%20immediately%20on%20detection%20of%20fraud%2C%20with%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%E2%80%9D.%20Even%20a%20child%20knows%20this%2C%20but%20my%20arrow%20was%20specifically%20aimed%20at%20%E2%80%9Ctwenty%20top%20fraudsters%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20known%20personally%20to%20the%20PM.%20Bankers%20said%20many%20of%20them%20dropped%20PM%E2%80%99s%20name%20and%20showed%20bankers%20their%20photos%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F07131838%2Fmodi-sitha.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20Narendra%20Modi%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22698%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F07131838%2Fmodi-sitha.png%20698w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F07131838%2Fmodi-sitha-300x150.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-484101%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22349%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%2FFiles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20minister%20evaded%20this%20query%20altogether%20as%20it%20may%20have%20endangered%20her%20job.%20But%20the%20same%20day%20her%20minister%20of%20state%20(MoS)%20Pankaj%20Chaudhary%20replied%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20has%20so%20far%20recovered%20Rs%2015%2C113%20crore%20from%20people%20accused%20under%20the%20Fugitive%20Economic%20Offenders%20Act%E2%80%9D.%20They%20owed%20over%20Rs%2040%2C000%20crore%2C%20so%20this%20means%20that%20they%20have%20avoided%20paying%20three-fourths%20of%20their%20dues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%205%20this%20year%2C%20another%20MoS%20of%20finance%2C%20Bhagwat%20Karad%2C%20replied%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20total%20exposure%20to%20top%2010%20borrowers%20from%20Scheduled%20Commercial%20Banks%20as%20reported%20in%20the%20Central%20Repository%20of%20Information%20on%20Large%20Credits%20(CRILC)%20database%20is%20Rs%2012%2C71%2C604%20crore%E2%80%9D.%20So%20we%20have%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20much%20banks%20have%20lent%20to%20just%20the%20top%2010%20borrowers%20and%20we%20estimate%20that%20the%20top%20100%20may%20have%20taken%20five%20to%20six%20times%20this%20amount.%20Of%20course%2C%20if%20they%20have%20the%20right%20contact%20and%20indulgence%2C%20a%20large%20part%20of%20this%20would%20never%20be%20returned%20to%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20precisely%20our%20point%2C%20and%20we%20find%20that%20banks%20have%20been%20saddled%20with%20some%2069%20lakh%20crore%20rupees%20of%20NPAs%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20nine%20years.%20It%20was%20never%20anywhere%20near%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20this%20amount%20during%20the%20previous%20nine%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPercentages%20of%20bad%20loans%20to%20total%20loans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20understand%20that%20bank%20loans%20have%20also%20gone%20up%20substantially%2C%20so%20percentages%20of%20bad%20loans%20to%20total%20loans%20may%20be%20a%20better%20indicator.%C2%A0These%20percentages%20can%20then%20be%20compared%20with%20similar%20percentages%20of%20NPA%20as%20part%20of%20total%20bank%20exposure.%20We%20will%20then%20better%20understand%20what%20is%20going%20on%20in%20India%20and%20why%20it%20is%20so%20suspicious%20and%20so%20much%20worse%20than%20other%20countries%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20percentages%20of%20NPA%20to%20total%20loans%20are%20on%20the%20IMF%20website%20%E2%80%93%20and%20they%20hover%20between%200.4%20and%201.4%20in%20advanced%20countries.%20Obviously%2C%20probity%20is%20higher%20there%2C%20cronyism%20is%20less%20and%20anti-corruption%20watch%20stronger.%20Italy%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20Portugal%20have%20more%20%E2%80%98buddy-ism%E2%80%99%20and%20such%20laxity%20increases%20their%20percentage%20of%20endangered%20loans%20to%20between%201%20and%201.5%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20site%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fglobaleconomy.com%5C%22%3Eglobaleconomy.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20gives%20more%20detailed%20data%20on%20developing%20countries.%20China%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20and%20Cambodia%20are%20all%20in%20the%201.6%20to%201.7%20percent%20range%20of%20bad%20loans%2C%20while%20in%20Indonesia%20it%20is%20at%202.6%20percent.%20NPAs%20are%20around%203%25%20of%20total%20loans%20in%20Turkey%2C%20Thailand%2C%20and%20Brunei.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20India%20is%20a%20disgrace%2C%20as%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20nine%20years%2C%20NPAs%20have%20usually%20been%207%25%20to%208%25%2C%20and%20according%20to%20the%20finance%20minister%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Cpeaked%20at%2011.46%25%20as%20on%2031.3.2018%E2%80%9D.%20In%202021%2C%20her%20MoS%20mentioned%20in%20another%20reply%20that%20the%20peak%20was%20actually%20%E2%80%9C12.17%25%20in%20the%20last%20seven%20years%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F19190118%2Ftrade-deficit-widens.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F19190118%2Ftrade-deficit-widens.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F19190118%2Ftrade-deficit-widens-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F09%2F19190118%2Ftrade-deficit-widens-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-292154%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECash.%20Photo%3A%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20short%20point%20is%20that%20if%20we%20assume%202%25%20of%20endangered%20loans%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20standard%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20percentage%20is%20so%20much%20higher%20in%20India.%20We%20submit%20that%20this%20was%20due%20to%20fraud%2C%20collusion%2C%20or%20abject%20misuse%20of%20bank%20loans%20and%20since%20nothing%20comes%20free%20some%20people%20were%20paid%20to%20%E2%80%9Croutinise%20losses%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%2C%20when%20NPAs%20reached%2011.46%25%20of%20total%20loans%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%2C%20some%209.46%25%20(i.e.%2C%20the%20percentage%20above%202)%20either%20went%20to%20line%20pockets%2C%20while%20maybe%20a%20fraction%20of%20this%20reflected%20the%20%E2%80%98constraints%E2%80%99%20in%20our%20banking%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEveryone%20says%2C%20no%20big%20loan%20is%20usually%20released%20without%20a%20political%20nod%20or%20a%20prod.%20During%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20some%20people%20may%20have%20been%20vigorously%20nodding%20their%20heads%2C%20left%20and%20right%2C%20like%20some%20agile%20Shiro-Bheda%20movement%20of%20Bharat%20Natyam%20dancers.%20Some%20may%20argue%20that%20the%20international%20standard%20of%202%25%20of%20loans%20turning%20sour%20is%20too%20harsh%20for%20India.%20But%20if%20most%20countries%20of%20the%20world%20that%20matter%20and%20other%20Asian%20countries%20can%20accommodate%20all%20causes%20for%20slippage%20in%20banking%20systems%20within%202%25%20(or%20slightly%20higher)%2C%20why%20cannot%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-modi-government-must-answer-for-indias-historic-bank-loss-of-rs-12-lakh-crore%5C%22%3EThe%20Modi%20Government%20Must%20Answer%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20Historic%20Bank%20Loss%20of%20Rs%2012%20Lakh%20Crore%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20the%20answer%2C%20we%20may%20use%20night-vision%20glasses%20to%20see%20how%20much%20has%20been%20siphoned%20off%20by%20known%20cronies%20and%20other%20criminals%20during%20the%20Modi%20years%20%E2%80%93%20tragically%2C%20without%20any%20retribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20now%20tomtoms%20that%20the%20percentage%20of%20NPAs%20to%20total%20advances%20came%20down%20to%204.41%25%20on%20December%2031%2C%202022.%20But%20the%20RBI%20predicts%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20gross%20NPA%20ratios%20of%20public%20sector%20banks%20may%20swell%20to%209.4%20percent%20in%20September%202023%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20fact%20that%20the%20upward%20movement%20of%20NPA%20percentages%20picked%20up%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20government%E2%80%99s%20years.%20But%20it%20was%20still%20below%203%25%2C%20going%20up%20to%204%25%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20There%20may%20have%20been%20some%20cases%20of%20reckless%20lending%20towards%20the%20end%2C%20but%20Modi%20had%20nine%20full%20years%20to%20scrutinise%2C%20stabilise%2C%20and%20exit%20bad%20loans.%20Instead%2C%20bad%20loans%20doubled%20and%20tripled%20in%20his%20time%2C%20with%20bank%20frauds%20committed%20by%20his%20known%20businessmen%20shooting%20through%20the%20roof.%20But%20all%20is%20well%20%E2%80%93%20because%20most%20voters%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20banking%20beyond%20the%20rates%20for%20deposits%20and%20home%2Fcar%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20move%20from%20NPAs%20to%20what%20money%20actually%20went%20up%20in%20smoke%20%E2%80%93%20as%20%E2%80%9Cwritten%20off%E2%80%9D%20forever.%20The%20government%20claims%20that%20banks%20indulge%20in%20this%20final%20write-offs%20%E2%80%9Cto%20clean%20up%20their%20balance%20sheets%2C%20avail%20tax%20benefits%20and%20optimise%20capital%E2%80%9D%20as%20directed%20by%20RBI.%20Frankly%2C%20these%20sound%20like%20%E2%80%98stuck%20records%E2%80%99%20of%20days%20gone%20by%20and%20their%20non-stop%20parroting%20of%20such%20date-expired%20wisdom%20is%20tantamount%20to%20covering%20up%20unprecedented%20losses.%20Because%20the%20losses%20are%20not%20made%20by%20the%20government%20but%20by%20ordinary%20bank%20customers%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20money%20lying%20with%20banks%20is%20%E2%80%9Cadjusted%E2%80%9D%20to%20cover%20up%20losses%20caused%20by%20racketeers%20and%20asset-suckers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20government%2C%20which%20pinches%20on%20every%20additional%20thousand%20crore%20rupees%20to%20the%20education%2C%20health%2C%20social%2C%20or%20rural%20employment%20sectors%2C%20wipes%20off%20Rs%2012.5%20lakh%20crores%20for%20non-repaid%20loans%20%E2%80%93%20without%20jailing%20any%20known%20scoundrel.%20Few%20realise%20this%20racket%20as%20no%20citizen%20is%20informed%20enough%20to%20question%20why%20this%20huge%20amount%20of%20%E2%80%9Cnon-recoverable%20losses%E2%80%9D%20was%20adjusted%20against%20their%20bank%20deposits%20and%20the%20hard-earned%20operating%20margins%20of%20banks.%20It%E2%80%99s%20all%20so%20atrociously%20neat%20and%20clean!%20We%20lost%2C%20they%20gained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoney%20hardly%20ever%20disappears%20%E2%80%93%20it%20travels%20from%20one%20pocket%20to%20the%20other.%20A%20section%20of%20defaulting%20(or%20embezzling)%20businessmen%20gain%20from%20these%20de%20facto%20waivers%20called%20write-offs%2C%20as%20the%20heat%20on%20their%20backs%20would%20be%20less.%20Those%20big%20sharks%20who%20finance%20any%20%E2%80%98helpful%E2%80%99%20political%20party%20can%20handle%20their%20matter%20quite%20neatly%20with%20precise%20%E2%80%9Ccorporate%20organisation%E2%80%9D%20and%20leave%20no%20trails%20of%20messy%20cash%20handling%20and%20fund%20transfers.%20Of%20course%2C%20if%20bankers%2C%20the%20enforcement%20directorate%2C%20the%20CBI%2C%20the%20directorate%20of%20revenue%20intelligence%2C%20the%20Serious%20Frauds%20Office%2C%20and%20other%20corporate%20and%20financial%20governance%20regulators%20are%20really%20serious%2C%20they%20can%20crack%20this%20modus%20operandi%2C%20very%20much%20like%20they%20hound%20cash%20transactions%20of%20the%20less%20sophisticated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20confirming%20the%20numbers%20of%20NPAs%20and%20write-offs%20that%20I%20had%20embedded%20in%20the%20parliament%20question%2C%20Sitharaman%20filled%20up%20a%20whole%20page%20with%20homilies%20supplied%20by%20some%20deputy%20secretary.%20On%20August%2018%2C%202022%2C%20the%20finance%20ministry%20confirmed%20more%20or%20less%20the%20statement%20supplied%20by%20the%20All%20India%20Bank%20Employees%20Association%20(AIBEA)%C2%A0%20that%20just%2013%20non-performing%20assets%20(ie%2C%20loss-making%20NPAs)%20blew%20up%20two-thirds%20of%20their%20total%20bank%20loans%20of%20Rs%204.47%20lakh%20crore.%20This%20is%20the%20type%20of%20probing%20query%20that%20the%20finance%20ministry%20is%20deflecting%20%E2%80%94%20because%2C%20frankly%2C%20political%20bosses%20shelter%20these%20embezzlers.%20PM%20Modi%20who%20goes%20around%20changing%20laws%20in%20bucketloads%20chose%20not%20to%20amend%20the%20existing%20financial%20laws%20that%20favour%20such%20felons.%20His%20latest%20insolvency%20resolution%20process%20ensures%20that%20banks%20can%20barely%20realise%20hardly%2040%20or%20so%20percent%20of%20their%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVideocon%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20had%20debts%20of%20Rs%2046%2C000%20crore.%20It%20was%20sold%20to%20Vedanta%20(a%20Modi%20acolyte%E2%80%99s%20company%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20odour)%20through%20this%20process%20for%20only%206%25%20of%20the%20claims.%20The%20Rs%2022%2C800%20crore%20debt%20of%20ABG%20Shipyard%20was%20put%20up%20for%20liquidation%20at%20just%205%25%20of%20its%20value%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20politically-connected%20owners%20had%20not%20only%20covered%20up%20repeated%20losses%20with%20fresh%20borrowings%20but%20had%20sucked%20out%20huge%20amounts%20of%20company%20funds%20for%20personal%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20if%20Modi%20and%20Sitharaman%20do%20not%20know%20how%20ineffectual%20their%20pith-sticks%20are%20on%20the%20thick%20backs%20of%20professional%20%E2%80%98bank%20robbers%E2%80%99%20who%20divert%20public%20money%20for%20their%20personal%20wealth%2C%20after%20satisfying%20those%20who%20matter%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fjawhar-sircar%5C%22%3EJawhar%20Sircar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20former%20Culture%20Secretary%20and%20CEO%20of%20Prasar%20Bharati.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691166398000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04213151%2FUntitled-design-2023-08-04T213108.167.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fthe-modi-govt-used-ordinary-indians-money-to-square-the-accounts-of-wilful-defaulters-fraudsters%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20banks%20in%20India%20lost%20Rs%2012%2C50%2C553%20crore%20during%20the%20nine-year%20Modi%20government.%20Never%20before%20in%20Indian%20history%20had%20banks%20lost%20such%20a%20gigantic%20amount%20without%20a%20whisper%20of%20a%20scam%20or%20any%20public%20debate%20of%20consequence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fthe-modi-govt-used-ordinary-indians-money-to-square-the-accounts-of-wilful-defaulters-fraudsters%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20Watch%20the%20Best%20Pee-wee%20Movies%20and%20Shows%20Online%3A%20From%20%E2%80%98Pee-Wee%E2%80%99s%20Playhouse%E2%80%99%20to%20%E2%80%98Pee-Wee%E2%80%99s%20Big%20Adventure%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691166284000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FTSDPEWE_CB004.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235687397%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Paul%20Reubens%2C%20who%20died%20July%2030%20after%20a%20six-year%20battle%20with%20cancer%2C%20is%20a%20pop-culture%20figure%20so%20entwined%20with%20the%20c