C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20a%20failed%20marriage%3F%20The%20one%20that%20ends%20in%20separation%20and%20divorce%20or%20that%20which%20continues%20despite%20-%20and%20sometimes%20because%20of%20-%20either%20or%20both%20partners%20breaking%20the%20covenant%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20first%20admit%20that%20the%20word%20'failed'%20has%20been%20used%20here%20as%20a%20clickbait.%20As%20my%20second%20and%20current%20husband%20once%20said-when%20I%20was%20dealing%20with%20the%20gut-wrenching%20experience%20of%20my%20'failed'%20first%20marriage-there%20is%20no%20Nobel%20Prize%20yet%20and%20likely%20will%20never%20be%20for%20accomplishing%20the%20great%20task%20of%20staying%20married.%20Marriage%20doesn't%20merit%20signifiers%20of%20the%20success%20framework.%20The%20sooner%20we%20learn%20it%2C%20the%20better%20it%20is%20for%20everyone%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20announced%20the%20end%20of%20his%20adult-18%20years%20old-marriage%20with%20Sophie%20Gregoire%20Trudeau.%20His%20father%20Pierre%20Trudeau%2C%20former%20PM%20of%20Canada%2C%20also%20separated%20from%20his%20wife%20while%20in%20office.%20When%20such%20high-profile%20and%20seemingly%20'successful'%20marriages%20end%2C%20they%20not%20only%20receive%20a%20disproportionate%20amount%20of%20attention%20but%20spawn%20a%20spate%20of%20comparisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bmeaningful%20and%20difficult%20conversation%26quot%3B%20about%20marriage%2C%20instead.%20The%20traditional%20view%20of%20companionate%20marriage%20(to%20keep%20the%20discourse%20under%20control%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20keep%20the%20%26quot%3Barranged%26quot%3B%20marriage%20out%20of%20its%20purview)%20is%20built%20on%20the%20primacy%20of%20promissory%20duty.%20When%20two%20people%20in%20love%20decide%20to%20get%20married%2C%20it%20is%20their%20promise%20of%20being%20together%20in%20good%20and%20bad%20times%2C%20while%20cherishing%2C%20loving%2C%20and%20honouring%20each%20other%2C%20which%20forms%20the%20bedrock%20of%20marriage.%20What%20does%20the%20separation%20of%20such%20individuals%20signify%3F%20At%20this%20point%2C%20let%20this%20be%20underscored%20that%20marriage%20of%20any%20kind%20ought%20to%20remain%20a%20private%20affair%20with%20only%20personal%20ethics%20governing%20it.%20No%20third%20person%20deserves%20a%20say%20in%20any%20marriage%20unless%20they%20are%20invited%20by%20one%20or%20both%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20marriage%20ends%2C%20the%20partner%20that%20initiates%20the%20conversation%20often%20becomes%20an%20Oppenheimer-like%20figure-the%20destroyer%20of%20worlds.%20Accusations%20of%20broken%20promise(s)%20are%20not%20uncommon%2C%20selfish%20motives%20are%20found%20or%20conjured%2C%20but%20most%20importantly%2C%20it%20is%20the%20dereliction%20of%20duty%20that%20is%20debated.%20Even%20in%20the%20individualism-driven%20Western%20world%2C%20the%20hard%20line%20view%20on%20marriage%20doesn't%20excuse%2C%20morally%20speaking%2C%20the%20rescinding%20of%20wedding%20vows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20a%20unilateral%20separation%20or%20divorce%2C%20unhappiness%20caused%20to%20the%20non-consenting%20spouse%20or%20children%20is%20still%20a%20morally%20charged%20subject.%20In%20a%20no-fault%20divorce%20scenario%2C%20permissibility%20is%20often%20at%20odds%20with%20morality.%20Just%20because%20something%20is%20allowed%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20one%20ought%20to%20do%20it.%20Like%20smoking%20on%20one's%20own%20balcony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%2C%20then%2C%20happens%20to%20a%20duty%20to%20oneself%20to%20prevent%20one's%20own%20unhappiness%3F%20Emmanuel%20Kant%20argued%2C%20and%20rather%20successfully%2C%20that%20unhappiness%20leads%20to%20vice.%20This%20and%20the%20adage%20that%20nothing%20pours%20out%20of%20an%20empty%20vessel%20hold%20truest%20in%20the%20case%20of%20marriage.%20Unhappiness%20need%20not%20be%20drastic%20or%20graphic%20or%20even%20visible.%20It%20is%20the%20invisible%20unhappiness%20of%20being%20that%20is%20the%20most%20corrosive%2C%20because%20rarely%20is%20it%20recognised%20and%20rarer%20still%20are%20the%20tools%20and%20mechanisms%20to%20cope%20with%20it.%20A%20marriage%20of%20unequal%20minds%2C%20however%20functional%20in%20familial%2C%20financial%20or%20fertility%20terms%2C%20is%20a%20good%20example%20of%20the%20breeding%20ground%20for%20such%20unhappiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%2C%20then%2C%20are%20people%20still%20hesitant%20in%20viewing%20marriage%20sans%20the%20aura%20of%20success%20and%20respectability%3F%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20liberal%2C%20radically%20evolved%20political%20minds%20practice%20this%20conservatism%20in%20their%20personal%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20hidden%20within%20the%20layers%20of%20guilt%20and%20shame%20that%20have%20ossified%20with%20centuries%20of%20conditioning.%20In%20human%20evolutionary%20history%2C%20it%20is%20but%20a%20short%20period.%20The%20nature%20and%20form%20of%20marriage%20have%20evolved%20over%20time.%20Communication%2C%20internal%20and%20external%2C%20about%20its%20relation%20to%20happiness%2C%20is%20yet%20to%20find%20a%20language%20that%20goes%20beyond%20the%20victimhood%20vocabulary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarriage%20is%20often%20seen%2C%20especially%20in%20our%20part%20of%20the%20world%2C%20as%20the%20panacea%20to%20all%20sorts%20of%20problems%20ranging%20from%20financial%20to%20psychological.%20However%2C%20not%20even%20the%20staunchest%20supporters%20of%20the%20institution%20are%20able%20to%20unequivocally%20locate%20it%20within%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20human%20pursuit%20of%20happiness.%20To%20use%20Marx%20in%20marriage-though%2C%20he%20ruminated%20extensively%20about%20marriage%2C%20family%20et%20al%20in%20his%20own%20writings-the%20mechanical%20materialism%20of%20life%20often%20overpowers%20social%20relations%20between%20spouses.%20Marx%20also%20said%2C%20in%20a%20different%20context%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20mutual%20value%20is%20for%20us%20the%20value%20of%20our%20mutual%20objects%26quot%3B%20and%20nothing%20defines%20better%20a%20merely%20duty-bound%20marriage%20that%20turns%20its%20back%20on%20individual%20fulfilment.%20One%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20Marxist%2C%20or%20even%20take%20Marx's%20ideas%20at%20face%20value%2C%20to%20fathom%20the%20unbearable%20weight%20of%20a%20relationship-an%20arrangement-that%20one%20is%20expected%20to%20carry%20purely%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20either%20duty%20or%20habit.%20No%20meaningful%20superstructure%20can%20be%20erected%20on%20such%20a%20mechanical%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20'successful'%20marriages%20successful%20only%20because%20there%20is%20a%20punitive%20aspect%20to%20their%20dissolution%3F%20While%20marrying%2C%20the%20partners%20agree%20to%20the%20legal%20default%20rules%20for%20the%20termination%20of%20their%20union.%20This%20is%20a%20problematic%20construct.%20What%20is%20a%20partnership%20actually%20worth%20if%20it%20needs%20such%20a%20regulatory%20framework%3F%20Does%20it%20not%20undermine%20agency%2C%20emotional%20and%20philosophical%3F%20Does%20it%20not%20turn%20marriage%20into%20a%20cold-blooded%20contract%20rather%20than%20a%20chosen%2C%20sanguine%20state%20of%20being%3F%20Does%20it%20not%20breed%20discontent%20and%20dishonesty%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20marriage%20may%20have%20its%20unique%20set%20of%20rules.%20As%20long%20as%20they%20are%20equal%20and%20followed%20by%20both%20partners%20with%20equal%20sincerity%2C%20there%20is%20still%20logic%20to%20the%20institution.%20When%20partners%20engage%20in%20clandestine%20sexual%20peccadilloes%20under%20the%20veneer%20of%20a%20'successful'%20marriage%20or%20bulldoze%20their%20value%20systems%20through%20the%20family%2C%20what%20is%20the%20success%20metric%20we%20are%20looking%20at%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20famous%20marry%20or%20separate%2C%20there%20may%20be%20a%20subliminal%20internalising%20of%20attached%20values%20by%20regular%20people.%20Marriage%2C%20with%20its%20essential%20linkages%20with%20sexual%20regulations%2C%20is%20an%20undemocratic%20space%20to%20start%20with.%20It%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20get%20lost%20in%20its%20labyrinth%20and%20be%20devoid%20of%20jouissance-the%20one%20thing%20that%20makes%20us%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nishtha%20Gautam%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691163180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-04%2Fdivorce-generic-istock_650x400_51523846403.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-difficult-conversation-failed-marriage-trudeau-split-and-the-family-oppenheimers-4270223%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20is%20a%20failed%20marriage%3F%20The%20one%20that%20ends%20in%20separation%20and%20divorce%20or%20that%20which%20continues%20despite%20-%20and%20sometimes%20because%20of%20-%20either%20or%20both%20partners%20breaking%20the%20covenant%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-difficult-conversation-failed-marriage-trudeau-split-and-the-family-oppenheimers-4270223%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-difficult-conversation-failed-marriage-trudeau-split-and-the-family-oppenheimers-4270223%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-difficult-conversation-failed-marriage-trudeau-split-and-the-family-oppenheimers-4270223%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20the%20Latest%20Trump%20Indictment%2C%20the%20US%20Enters%20a%20Simmering%20Civil%20Cold%20War%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F31084936%2FDonald_Trump_29496131773.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F08%2F01%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-jan-6-indictment-2020-election-annotated.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20indictment%2C%20for%20his%20role%20in%20the%20January%206%2C%202021%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Capitol%20as%20part%20of%20an%20insurrection%20against%20the%20US%20constitution%2C%20is%20damning%2C%20serious%2C%20but%20also%20limited%2C%20despite%20what%20many%20media%20outlets%20are%20claiming%20(largely%20by%20omission).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20indictment%20focuses%20on%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20democracy%20itself%2C%20it%20fails%20to%20say%20anything%20about%20his%20most%20serious%20crime%3A%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20overthrow%20the%20government%20by%20force%20and%20remain%20in%20power%20despite%20losing%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20principally%20focuses%20on%20the%20charge%20that%20Trump%20%3Cem%3Etook%20advantage%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20the%20January%206%20protests%20%3Cem%3Erather%20than%20having%20orchestrated%2C%20organised%2C%20and%20conspired%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20others%20across%20the%20GOP%20as%20well%20as%20numerous%20openly%20armed%20fascistic%20and%20white%20supremacist%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20Oath%20Keepers%20and%20Proud%20Boys%20(who%20regarded%20Trump%20as%20their%20leader%20and%20inspiration).%20The%20latter%20groups%E2%80%99%20members%20and%20leaders%20in%20fact%20have%20been%20jailed%20for%20seditious%20conspiracy%20(which%20is%20the%20organisation%20stage%20of%20open%20treason)%20for%20their%20violent%20actions%20before%20and%20on%20January%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20this%3F%20This%20is%20a%20key%20question%20largely%20unaddressed%20by%20most%20media%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F06%2F19%2Ffbi-resisted-opening-probe-into-trumps-role-jan-6-more-than-year%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20investigation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20June%2019%2C%202023%20revealed%20that%20the%20FBI%20(led%20by%20Trump%20appointee%20Christopher%20Wray)%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20under%20Biden-appointee%20Merrick%20Garland%2C%20did%20little%20or%20nothing%20to%20investigate%20Trump%20and%20his%20immediate%20circle%20for%20over%20a%20year%20after%20January%206%2C%20so%20as%20not%20to%20appear%20%E2%80%9Cpartisan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20took%20almost%20two%20years%20to%20get%20to%20this%20current%20indictment.%20Why%3F%20There%20are%20three%20likely%20reasons%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20The%20two%20main%20US%20political%20parties%2C%20despite%20public%20rhetoric%2C%20etc%2C%20are%20largely%20similar%20in%20philosophy%20and%20corporate%20backing%2C%20with%20due%20respect%20to%20differing%20electoral%20constituencies%20that%20they%20have%20to%20keep%20satisfied%2C%20mainly%20through%20rhetoric.%20Hence%2C%20they%20are%20interdependent%20and%20seek%20to%20maintain%20one%20another%2C%20even%20protect%20one%20another%2C%20especially%20from%20mass%20popular%20opposition.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20national%20security%20state%20%E2%80%93%20FBI%2C%20CIA%2C%20national%20guard%2C%20law%20enforcement%20in%20general%20%E2%80%93%20are%20core%20elements%20of%20the%20American%20imperial%20state%2C%20and%20are%20in%20the%20care%20of%20the%20two%20main%20parties.%20Their%20own%20activities%20and%20collaborations%20with%20Trump%20and%20failures%20to%20take%20security%20precautions%20ahead%20of%20January%206%2C%202021%20enabled%20the%20storming%20of%20the%20Capitol%20building%20by%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20supporters.%20They%20have%20no%20incentive%20to%20thoroughly%20investigate%20their%20own%20collusion%20with%20Trump.%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20calls%20for%20bipartisanship%20and%20a%20strong%20GOP%20further%20evidence%20this%20trend%2C%20as%20does%20failure%20to%20expeditiously%20indict%20and%20prosecute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20build-up%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20US%20policy%20towards%20it%20%E2%80%93%20armed%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20required%20bipartisan%20support%20in%20House%20and%20Senate.%20Prosecuting%20Trump%20took%20a%20back%20seat%20during%20that%20process.%20The%20spring%20offensive%20has%20gone%20badly%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20indicting%20Trump%20plays%20well%2C%20especially%20as%20he%E2%80%99s%20regarded%20by%20establishment%20elites%20to%20be%20too%20unpredictable%20to%20be%20back%20at%20the%20helm%20(given%20his%20pro-Russian%20views).%20But%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20popularity%20among%20GOP%20voters%20means%20he%20remains%20influential%20and%20a%20source%20of%20disruption%2C%20a%20force%20of%20nature%20not%20easily%20controlled%2C%20a%20power%20partially%20created%20by%20appeasement%20within%20a%20US%20ruling%20elite%20that%20is%20increasingly%20moving%20to%20the%20authoritarian%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20Finally%2C%20the%20Democratic%20party%E2%80%99s%202024%20programme%20rests%20strongly%20on%20the%20GOP%20and%20most%20likely%20a%20Trump%20candidacy.%20The%20fear%20of%20Trump%20is%20a%20major%20motivator%20of%20Democratic%20voter%20turnout%2C%20as%20well%20as%20of%20independent%20voters%20who%20will%20most%20likely%20swing%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20pages%20of%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20attack%20on%20constitutional%20norms%20in%20Brazil%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Festablishment-liberals-far-right-extremism%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20writer%20noted%20the%20following%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20remains%20the%20case%20in%20the%20current%20context%3A%20Establishment%20liberals%20%E2%80%93%20who%20publicly%20take%20up%20the%20mantle%20of%20defenders%20of%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20are%20unreliable%20allies%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20fascism.%20They%20fear%20mass%20anti-fascist%20marches%20and%20movements%20far%20more%20than%20they%20fear%20fascism%20because%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20liberalism%20is%20a%20theory%20of%20government%2C%20economy%20and%20society%20that%20is%20elitist%2C%20top-down%2C%20anti-democratic%2C%20corporate-backed%2C%20and%20tied%20into%20the%20neoliberal%20project%20in%20all%20its%20essentials.%20And%20massive%20resistance%20to%20all%20those%20forces%20and%20factors%20has%20been%20mounting%20across%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20why%20neoliberal%20establishments%20and%20their%20allies%20turn%20to%20authoritarianism%20and%20fascism%20to%20divide%20people%20on%20lines%20of%20race%2C%20ethnicity%2C%20religion%20or%20other%20elite-cultivated%20cleavages%20in%20the%20social%20fabric%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-521330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAttack%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20by%20Donald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20on%20January%206%2C%202021.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20fascists%20and%20far-right%20groups%20scream%20about%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Left%E2%80%99%20and%20minorities%20and%20immigrants%2C%20liberals%20downplay%20fascist%20threats%2C%20disarm%20ordinary%20people%2C%20and%20enable%20more%20and%20more%20restrictive%20and%20undemocratic%20legislation%20%E2%80%93%20strengthening%20police%20and%20border%20force%20powers%2C%20restricting%20voting%20rights%20and%20rights%20or%20legitimate%20protest.%20We%20see%20this%20most%20starkly%20in%20the%20way%20protesting%20workers%20and%20minorities%20are%20policed%20in%20contrast%20with%20how%20violent%20right-wing%20forces%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2021%2Fjan%2F06%2Fcapitol-mob-police-trump-george-floyd-protests-photos%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etreated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20argued%20by%20establishment%20liberals%20in%20both%20Brazil%20and%20the%20US%20that%20prosecuting%20either%20Jair%20Bolsonaro%20or%20Donald%20Trump%20would%20be%20politically%20provocative%20and%20cause%20more%20far-right%20and%20fascist%20violence.%20But%20we%20also%20know%20that%20where%20US%20Democrats%20govern%20cities%20and%20states%20during%20periods%20of%20mass%20rebellion%20and%20protest%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20those%20following%20the%20police%20murder%20of%20George%20Floyd%20%E2%80%93%20they%20have%20no%20qualms%20in%20ordering%20massive%20policing%20to%20quell%20peaceful%20protests.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2021%2F03%2F01%2Fjudas-and-the-black-messiah-and-the-klan-act%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehistorically%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20treatment%20by%20the%20FBI%20of%20the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20and%20of%20the%20Black%20Panther%20Party%20was%20repressive%2C%20murderous%2C%20sustained%2C%20and%20anti-democratic.%20The%20white%20supremacist%20Ku%20Klux%20Klan%20on%20the%20other%20hand%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20to%20separate%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%20in%20those%20regards%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20whatever%20their%20political%20rhetoric%20may%20be.%20This%20is%20rooted%20in%20a%20consensus%20over%20the%20basic%20fundamentals%20of%20US%20society%20%E2%80%93%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%98fair%E2%80%99%2C%20that%20the%20system%20%E2%80%98works%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20mass%20protest%20against%20forces%20that%20protect%20the%20corporate-dominated%20status%20quo%20is%20irrational%20and%20dangerous%20and%20must%20be%20suppressed%20or%20lulled%20or%20deceived%20into%20thinking%20the%20fascist%20danger%20is%20over-played%20or%20has%20been%20quelled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20CV%20from%20Goodfellas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%E2%80%99s%20CV%20now%20reads%20as%20especially%20damning%3A%20investigated%20while%20in%20office%20on%20charges%20of%20collaboration%20with%20Russia%3B%20two%20impeachments%20by%20the%20House%3B%20an%20insurrection%20and%20coup%20attempt%20to%20overturn%20the%20Constitution%20on%206%20January%202021%3B%20and%20several%20other%20charges%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%E2%80%99s%20self-image%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98goodfella%20has%20been%20given%20a%20further%20lease%20of%20life.%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20more%20to%20come%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20the%20investigation%20of%20attempts%20to%20steal%20the%202020%20election%20in%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20broader%20note%2C%20the%20whole%20saga%20is%20an%20indictment%20of%20the%20criminality%20of%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20his%20personalist%20form%20of%20presidential%20power%20as%20if%20he%20owned%20the%20US%20government%20as%20he%20runs%20the%20Trump%20Organisation%2C%20of%20the%20far%20right%20GOP%20that%20continues%20to%20back%20him.%20One%20half%20of%20the%20two-party%20US%20political%20system%20has%20turned%20its%20back%20on%20the%20basic%20tenets%20of%20the%20US%20constitution%20let%20alone%20democracy%20itself.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Democrats%20lack%20a%20sufficiently%20authentic%20and%20attractive%20programme%20to%20present%20to%20the%20electorate%2C%20which%20faces%20multiple%20hardships%20regardless%20of%20party%20affiliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJanuary%206%2C%202021%20%E2%80%93%20a%20major%20turning%20point%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajor%20issues%20were%20raised%20by%20the%20events%20and%20immediate%20aftermath%20of%20January%206%2C%202021.%20It%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26989815%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuggested%20by%20this%20writer%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CPresident%20Donald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20attempted%20coup%20and%20insurrection%E2%80%99s%20political%20effects%20are%20set%20to%20continue%20in%20the%20future%20because%20the%20enabling%20conditions%20have%20deep%20historical%20roots%2C%20its%20support%20reaches%20far%20into%20the%20U.S.%20state%2C%20broad%20sections%20of%20the%20Republican%20Party%20and%20electorate%2C%20military%2C%20and%20law%20enforcement.%20It%20will%20have%20national%20and%20global%20implications.%20There%20is%20a%20feeling%20that%20the%20imperial%20homeland%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20descent%20into%20the%20abyss.%20Although%20the%20U.S.%20political%20system%20appears%20to%20have%20squeaked%20through%20a%20major%20stress%20test%2C%20the%20political%20reverberations%20of%20Trumpism%20will%20remain%20for%20some%20time%20to%20come.%20There%20is%20no%20%E2%80%98return%20to%20normalcy%E2%80%99%20the%20country%20craves%20for%2C%20without%20reforms%20to%20a%20system%20that%20advantages%20the%20politics%20of%20extremism%20in%20the%20Republican%20Party.%20President%20Biden%20has%20the%20challenge%20and%20opportunity%20to%20extirpate%20Trumpism%20and%20white%20supremacy%20from%20the%20U.S.%20body%20politic%20%E2%80%93but%20does%20he%20have%20the%20political%20will%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20latest%20indictment%20against%20former%20president%20Trump%20suggests%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-barbara-walter-america-civil-war-fascism%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshift%20towards%20fascistic%20authoritarianism%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20establishment%E2%80%99s%20core%20parties%20and%20institutions%20has%20become%20institutionalised.%20The%20United%20States%20is%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20simmering%20civil%20cold%20war%2C%20divided%2C%20factionalised%2C%20and%20unstable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECan%20it%20still%20be%20regarded%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfree%20world%E2%80%9D%20and%20champion%20of%20democracy%20against%20autocracy%3F%20A%20reliable%20partner%20for%20its%20international%20allies%20and%20partners%3F%20A%20land%20of%20opportunity%20and%20hope%20embodied%20in%20the%20American%20dream%3F%20Or%20is%20its%20crisis%20of%20authority%20and%20factionalisation%20so%20deep%20that%20there%20appears%20no%20way%20out%20this%20morass%20any%20time%20soon%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%2016%20months%20running%20up%20to%20the%202024%20elections%20is%20shaping%20up%20as%20focused%20on%20a%20former%20president%20and%20candidate%20making%20numerous%20court%20appearances%20and%20accusing%20the%20legal%20system%20of%20being%20weaponised%20against%20him.%20And%20an%20aging%20liberal%20with%20a%20record%20that%E2%80%99s%20better%20than%20expected%20but%20considered%20too%20little%20too%20late%2C%20whose%20main%20claim%20will%20be%20what%20it%20was%20in%202020%3A%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmericans%20like%20to%20think%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctree%20of%20liberty%E2%80%9D%20is%20nourished%20by%20the%20blood%20of%20patriotic%20martyrs.%20What%20happens%20if%20that%20tree%20comes%20crashing%20down%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20Fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3EThe%20Wire%3Ci%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691162873000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F31084936%2FDonald_Trump_29496131773.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwith-the-latest-trump-indictment-the-us-enters-a-simmering-civil-cold-war%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20shift%20towards%20fascistic%20authoritarianism%20in%20the%20US%20establishment%E2%80%99s%20core%20parties%20and%20institutions%20has%20become%20institutionalised.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwith-the-latest-trump-indictment-the-us-enters-a-simmering-civil-cold-war%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Savarkar%20script%20registered%20with%20Randeep%20%26%20Utkarsh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691162332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102432135%2Cimgsize-71534.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fswatantrya-veer-savarkar-rights-controversy-producer-sandeep-singh-registered-the-films-script-with-randeep-hooda-and-utkarsh-naithani-credited-as-writers%2Farticleshow%2F102432173.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102432173.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20update%20on%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20Sandeep%20Singh%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20stake%20claim%20on%20the%20project%2C%20took%20the%20same%20script%20and%20changed%20the%20title%20spelling%20before%20registering%20it%20under%20his%20name%20with%20the%20SWA%20on%20November%2021%2C%20thus%20claiming%20to%20be%20the%20author.%22%2C%22author%22%