123080400703_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-insolvency-nclt-directs-rp-to-file-details-on-recent-developments-123080400703_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Upholds%20ASI%20Survey%20of%20Gyanvapi%20Premises%2C%20Tells%20Authorities%20to%20Follow%20'Non-Invasive'%20Processes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%2C%20August%204%2C%20upheld%20an%20order%20by%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20allowing%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20to%20conduct%20its%20investigation%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20in%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20as%20well%20as%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20was%20hearing%20a%20petition%20by%20the%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masjid%20Committee%20%E2%80%93%20which%20manages%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20%E2%80%93%20challenging%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20August%203%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20order%20had%20in%20turn%20upheld%20a%20July%2021%20order%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court%20ordering%20the%20ASI%20survey%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20intended%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20the%20mosque%20had%20been%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EASI%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fasi-to-start-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-from-early-morning-friday-even-as-muslim-side-approaches-sc%5C%22%3Earrived%20at%20the%20site%20early%20on%20Friday%20morning%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20begin%20their%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20the%20masjid%20committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%20means%20that%20the%20ASI%20will%20continue%20examining%20the%20controversial%20religious%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20three-judge%20bench%20ordered%20the%20archaeological%20body%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20survey%20through%20%E2%80%9Cnon-invasive%E2%80%9D%20processes%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-allows-asi-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-without-excavation-or-damage-to-structure-using-non-invasive-process-234398%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20committee%20had%20planned%20to%20boycott%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20but%20journalist%20Omar%20Rashid%20tweeted%20on%20Friday%20afternoon%20that%20it%20has%20decided%20to%20cooperate%20with%20it%20in%20light%20of%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EJust%20in%3A%20After%20initially%20boycotting%20the%20ASI%20survey%20of%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%2C%20its%20caretakers%20now%2C%20following%20the%20SC%20upholding%20the%20survey%2C%20have%20decided%20to%20co-operate%20with%20ASI%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Muslim%20party%20hopes%20the%20survey%20will%20be%20carried%20out%20in%20an%20impartial%20manner%2C%20without%20hurting%20the%20mosque%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fseemay%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40seemay%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Omar%20Rashid%20(%40omar7rashid)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fomar7rashid%2Fstatus%2F1687429304794370048%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%204%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepresenting%20the%20committee%20in%20the%20top%20court%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Huzefa%20Ahmadi%20had%20argued%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%2C%201991%20%E2%80%93%20which%20prohibits%20altering%20the%20religious%20character%20of%20a%20place%20of%20worship%20as%20it%20existed%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20violated%20if%20the%20survey%20was%20conducted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20ordering%20the%20survey%2C%20and%20by%20going%20back%20in%20the%20history%20as%20to%20what%20happened%20500%20years%20ago%2C%20are%20you%20not%20violating%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%3F%E2%80%9D%20Ahmadi%20asked%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhen%20you%20start%20a%20survey%2C%20you%20are%20unravelling%20the%20wounds%20of%20the%20past.%20And%20it%20is%20the%20very%20same%20thing%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20%5BAct%5D%20seeks%20to%20prohibit%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Justice%20Pardiwala%20told%20Ahmadi%20that%20if%20the%20suit%20stating%20that%20the%20mosque%20houses%20Hindu%20deities%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20prompted%20the%20Varanasi%20court%20to%20order%20the%20ASI%20survey%20%E2%80%93%20is%20not%20found%20to%20be%20maintainable%2C%20the%20results%20of%20the%20survey%20would%20not%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsider%20it%20from%20a%20different%20angle.%20Your%20principal%20argument%20is%20why%20undertake%20the%20survey%20when%20the%20suit%E2%80%99s%20maintainability%20is%20questioned.%20This%20survey%20is%20going%20to%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20report.%20Tomorrow%2C%20if%20you%20succeed%20in%20getting%20the%20plaint%20rejected%2C%20this%20survey%20will%20be%20nothing%20but%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20the%20survey%20take%20place%20because%20of%20the%20assurance%20given%20by%20Mr.%20Mehta%20that%20there%20is%20no%20invasive%20method.%20Let%20the%20report%20be%20given%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20also%20said%20that%20the%20mosque%20side%20will%20be%20able%20to%20challenge%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20findings%20if%20they%20wished%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20Mr.%20Ahmadi%2C%20this%20is%20an%20interlocutory%20order%20appointing%20a%20commissioner.%20Why%20should%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20interfere%3F%20We%20will%20keep%20open%20all%20issues%20regarding%20maintainability%2C%20objections%20to%20commission%20evidence%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CEven%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20case%2C%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20argument%20was%20made%20on%20the%20evidentiary%20value%20of%20ASI%20survey.%20These%20are%20issues%20to%20be%20addressed%20at%20the%20final%20hearing%20as%20to%20what%20is%20the%20evidentiary%20value%20of%20the%20survey.%20We%20will%20safeguard%20the%20structure.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Funderstanding-the-gyanvapi-mosque-dispute-what-does-the-places-of-worship-act-say%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Case%3A%20What%20Does%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20Act%20Say%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20masjid%20committee%20has%20also%20expressed%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20survey%20might%20damage%20parts%20of%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20beginning%2C%20we%20have%20had%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20building%20may%20get%20damaged%20because%20it%20is%20an%20old%20structure.%20We%20claim%20it%20is%20600%20years%20old.%20The%20other%20side%20claims%20that%20it%20is%20even%20older%20%E2%80%93%201%2C000%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Farman%20Naqvi%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20committee%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fasi-to-start-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-from-early-morning-friday-even-as-muslim-side-approaches-sc%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20building%20is%20not%20made%20from%20modern%20material%20or%20with%20modern%20technology.%20If%20a%20loose%20brick%20falls%20from%20somewhere%2C%20who%20will%20be%20responsible%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said%20that%20given%20the%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20assurances%20that%20no%20damage%20would%20occur%2C%20it%20was%20not%20inclined%20to%20stop%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20clarified%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20ASI%20by%20solicitor%20general%20of%20India%20Mr.%20Tushar%20Mehta%20that%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20the%20entire%20survey%20will%20be%20completed%20without%20any%20excavation%20at%20the%20site%20and%20without%20causing%20any%20destruction%20to%20the%20structure%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%E2%80%99s%20order%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-allows-asi-survey-of-gyanvapi-mosque-without-excavation-or-damage-to-structure-using-non-invasive-process-234398%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20temple%20side%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Madhavi%20Divan%20also%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUltimately%2C%20it%20is%20the%20ASI.%20Its%20job%20is%20to%20preserve%20monuments%20%E2%80%A6%20so%20surely%20they%20cannot%20damage%20it.%20They%20know%20better.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%E2%80%99s%20order%20continued%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20order%20of%20the%20learned%20trial%20judge%20passed%20under%20Order%2026%20Rule%2010A%20of%20the%20CPC%20cannot%20be%20prima%20facie%20at%20this%20stage%20to%20be%20said%20as%20without%20jurisdiction%20%E2%80%A6%20Having%20regard%20to%20the%20nature%20and%20ambit%20of%20a%20Court-appointed%20commissioners%2C%20we%20are%20unable%20to%20differ%20with%20the%20view%20of%20the%20High%20Court%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20jurisdiction%20under%20Article%20136.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691160291000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-greenlights-asi-gyanvapi-survey%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20mosque%20side%20said%20it%20has%20apprehensions%20that%20the%20building%20may%20get%20damaged%20due%20to%20the%20survey%2C%20claiming%20that%20it%20is%20a%20600-year-old%20structure.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-greenlights-asi-gyanvapi-survey%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20signs%20law%20on%20barring%20'unfriendly'%20foreigners%20from%20owning%20stakes%20in%20Russian%20firms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691160107000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102431526%2Cimgsize-495487.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-signs-law-on-barring-unfriendly-foreigners-from-owning-stakes-in-russian-firms%2Farticleshow%2F102431528.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102431528.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20signed%20a%20law%20allowing%20for%20foreign%20investors%20from%20%26quot%3Bunfriendly%26quot%3B%20countries%20to%20be%20barred%20from%20holding%20stakes%20in%20major%20Russian%20companies%20and%20banks%2C%20state%20news%20agency%20RIA%20said%20on%20Friday.%20It%20said%20the%20government%20would%20draw%20up%20a%20list%20of%20Russian%20firms%20to%20be%20covered%20by%20the%20law%2C%20including%20all%20systemically%20important%20banks%20and%20firms%20above%20a%20certain%20size%20in%20terms%20of%20revenue%2C%20employees%2C%20assets%20or%20taxes%20paid.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-signs-law-on-barring-unfriendly-foreigners-from-owning-stakes-in-russian-firms%2Farticleshow%2F102431528.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-signs-law-on-barring-unfriendly-foreigners-from-owning-stakes-in-russian-firms%2Famp_articleshow%2F102431528.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-signs-law-on-barring-unfriendly-foreigners-from-owning-stakes-in-russian-firms%2Famp_articleshow%2F102431528.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%202019%20Election%20Was%20One-Sided%2C%20%5C%22Manipulation%5C%22%20Wouldn't%20Help%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20research%20paper%20by%20Sabyasachi%20Das%20from%20Ashoka%20University%20titled%20%26quot%3BDemocratic%20Backsliding%20in%20the%20World's%20Largest%20Democracy%26quot%3B%20suggests%20that%20there%20was%20manipulation%20of%20results%20in%20some%20seats%20by%20the%20ruling%20BJP%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20party%20winning%20a%20disproportionately%20higher%20share%20of%20closely-contested%20constituencies%20in%20the%202019%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20created%20a%20political%20furore%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20opposition%20firing%20guns%20at%20each%20other.%20Such%20a%20paper%20just%20before%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20has%20raised%20many%20eyebrows%2C%20as%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20known%20globally%20for%20its%20process%20and%20in%20India%20for%20its%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20has%20been%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20opposition%20to%20create%20a%20perception%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%202019%20election%20was%20a%20closely%20contested%20one%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBJP%20won%20a%20high%20share%20of%20closely%20contested%20seats%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBJP%20won%20a%20high%20share%20of%20these%20seats%20due%20to%20manipulation%20in%20states%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAnd%20so%20its%20victory%20in%202019%20is%20questionable%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%20No.%201%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20of%20the%20survey%20suggest%20this%20alleged%20manipulation%20had%20an%20impact%20only%20on%20nine%20to%2018%20seats%2C%20considering%20a%20victory%20margin%20of%203%25%20to%207%25.%20Normally%205%25%20is%20considered%20a%20close%20contest%2C%207%25%20a%20decent%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20election%2C%20a%205%25%20victory%20margin%20corresponded%20to%20an%20average%2056%2C000%20votes%20while%207%25%2C%20to%20around%2079%2C000%20votes.%20Even%20if%20we%20take%20the%20findings%20at%20face%20value%2C%20it%20doesn't%20impact%20the%20overall%20results%20as%20the%20BJP%20won%20303%20seats%20out%20of%20543.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20we%20consider%2018%20seats%20where%20results%20were%20manipulated%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20285%20seats%20fair%20and%20square%2C%20which%20is%20way%20above%20the%20majority%20of%20272%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%20No.%202%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20says%20the%20BJP%20won%20a%20disproportionately%20higher%20number%20of%20closely%20contested%20seats%20and%20that%20too%20in%20states%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power.%20The%20author%20argues%20that%20manipulation%20is%20local%20at%20the%20booth%20level%2C%20and%20implies%20that%20manipulation%20could%20be%20concentrated%20in%20constituencies%20that%20have%20a%20high%20share%20of%20observers%20who%20are%20state%20civil%20service%20officers%20from%20BJP-ruled%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20election%2C%2098%20seats%20were%20closely%20contested%3B%20the%20victory%20margin%20was%20less%20than%205%25.%20Of%20these%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20only%2043%2C%20which%20is%20roughly%2044%25%20or%20less%20than%20half.%20The%20Congress%20won%2019%20of%20these%20closely%20contested%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2043%20seats%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%2022%20in%20states%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power.%20All%20but%20one%20were%20won%20from%20non-BJP%20ruled%20states%20like%20Karnataka%20(4)%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20(2)%2C%20Telangana%20(1)%2C%20Odisha%20(6)%2C%20West%20Bengal%20(7)%2C%20and%20Punjab%20(1).%20So%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20seats%20that%20the%20BJP%20won%20from%20states%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power%20to%20those%20where%20it%20was%20not%20in%20power%20is%20almost%2050-50.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20129%20out%20of%20its%20303%20tally%20from%20states%20where%20it%20was%20not%20in%20power.%20The%20election%20was%20in%20no%20way%20a%20closely%20contested%20one%20as%20the%20BJP%20recorded%20more%20than%20a%2050%20per%20cent%20vote%20share%20on%20224%20seats%2C%20which%20is%20roughly%2075%25%20of%20its%20tally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%20No.%203%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20is%20hinting%20that%20the%20BJP%20was%20able%20to%20manipulate%20results%20in%20seats%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20observers%20who%20were%20state%20civil%20service%20officers.%20However%2C%20if%20this%20is%20true%20and%20so%20easy%2C%20then%20the%20BJP's%20record%20in%20state%20elections%20where%20it%20was%20the%20incumbent%20should%20be%20fantastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20case.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20BJP's%20performance%20in%20states%20where%20it%20was%20incumbent%20was%20poorer%20than%20states%20where%20it%20was%20in%20the%20opposition.%20The%20party%20lost%20more%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Karnataka%20and%20Himachal%2C%20where%20it%20was%20in%20power%20over%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%20No.%204%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClosely%20contested%20seats%20can%20be%20won%20due%20to%20numerous%20reasons%20like%20organisational%20strength%2C%20caste%20arithmetic%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20alliances%20and%20the%20campaign.%20To%20further%20his%20point%20that%20these%20seats%20were%20won%20due%20to%20electoral%20manipulation%20and%20not%20precise%20control%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20incumbent%20party's%20ability%20to%20precisely%20predict%20and%20affect%20win%20margins%20through%20campaigning%2C%20the%20author%20uses%20NES%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20measures%20campaigning%20in%20the%20form%20of%20door-to-door%20visits%20by%20the%20BJP%20and%20other%20political%20parties%20to%20directly%20test%20for%20precise%20control.%20He%20finds%20that%20neither%20the%20BJP%20nor%20any%20other%20party%20campaigned%20significantly%20harder%20in%20constituencies%20that%20the%20BJP%20barely%20won.%20Therefore%2C%20precise%20control%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20primary%20mechanism%20for%20such%20wins.%20To%20use%20only%20door%20to%20door%20visits%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20the%20entire%20campaign%20is%20not%20apt%2C%20as%20traditional%20%2F%20modern%20campaign%20mediums%20like%20events%2C%20rallies%2C%20town%20halls%2C%20social%20%2F%20digital%20campaigns%20etc.%20are%20ignored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20quantify%20qualitative%20aspects%20like%20the%20impact%20of%20campaigning%2C%20the%20image%20of%20the%20local%20candidate%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20caste%2C%20alliances%2C%20organization%20strength%2C%20motivation%20of%20cadre%2C%20quality%20of%20leadership%20and%20campaigns%20by%20stars%20on%20election%20results%2C%20so%20this%20point%20is%20not%20very%20conclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%20No.%205%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20references%20a%20Quint%20article%20of%202019%2C%20which%20points%20to%20the%20variance%20in%20votes%20polled%20in%20Electronic%20Voting%20Machines%20and%20the%20votes%20counted.%20The%20article%20mentions%20373%20seats%20where%20there%20was%20such%20a%20variance.%20However%2C%20the%20key%20question%20is%2C%20how%20many%20of%20these%20the%20BJP%20won.%20The%20list%20of%20those%20373%20seats%20is%20not%20available.%20The%20article%20gives%20examples%20of%2011%20such%20seats%20where%20there%20were%20discrepancies.%20Of%20these%2C%20five%20were%20won%20by%20the%20BJP%20and%20six%20by%20others%20-%20four%20by%20the%20DMK%20and%20one%20each%20by%20the%20BJD%20and%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conclusions%20of%20the%20paper%2C%20therefore%2C%20are%20not%20conclusive%2C%20as%20the%20above%20arguments%20show.%20The%20research%20lacks%20rigour%20and%20the%20claims%20not%20substantiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20by%20picking%20up%20this%20issue%20and%20asking%20ECI%20to%20respond%20is%20like%20shooting%20itself%20in%20the%20foot%20as%20the%20author%20himself%20has%20absolved%20ECI.%20This%20also%20takes%20the%20focus%20away%20from%20real%20issues.%20Congress%20has%20not%20learnt%20its%20lessons%20from%20Rafael%2C%20Pegasus%2C%20these%20academic%20issues%20do%20not%20really%20move%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuestioning%20the%20protector%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20(ECI)%20when%20you%20have%20recently%20won%20an%20election%20in%20Karnataka%20resoundingly%20doesn't%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691160000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-03%2Fu7g8no5o_bjp-generic_625x300_30_March_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2F2019-election-was-one-sided-manipulation-wouldnt-help-4270080%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20research%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3BDemocratic%20Backsliding%20in%20the%20World's%20Largest%20Democracy%26quot%3B%20suggests%20that%20there%20was%20manipulation%20of%20results%20in%20some%20seats%20by%20the%20ruling%20BJP.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fop