wn%20as%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Italy%20there%20are%20one%20million%20people%20who%20recovered%20from%20cancer%2C%20Foreign%20Minister%20Antonio%20Tajani%20also%20said%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20who%20have%20defeated%20cancer%20cannot%20be%20branded%20for%20life%20as%20second-class%20citizens%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Giorgia%20Meloni%20said%20her%20right-wing%20government%20would%20offer%20the%20necessary%20support%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20RTBF%20law%20gets%20approved%20in%20%26quot%3Bthe%20shortest%20time%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposals%20would%20allow%20recovering%20cancer%20patients%20not%20to%20share%20information%20about%20their%20previous%20condition%20with%20financial%20institutions%2C%20or%20adoption%20authorities%2C%20provided%20that%205-10%20years%20had%20passed%20since%20the%20successful%20end%20of%20their%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20laws%20are%20already%20in%20place%20in%20France%2C%20Luxembourg%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Belgium%20and%20Portugal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Italian%20Medical%20Oncology%20Association%20(AIOM).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691151960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Fatt9hsso_court-generic_625x300_27_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcancer-survivors-right-to-be-forgotten-bill-passed-in-italy-lower-house-4269268%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Italian%20law%20giving%20cancer%20survivors%20the%20right%20not%20to%20declare%20their%20past%20condition%20to%20banks%20and%20insurance%20agencies%2C%20shielding%20them%20from%20discrimination%2C%20has%20been%20approved%20by%20the%20lower%20house%20of%20parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%2