ng-case-123080400240_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Salute%20to%20Achyut%20Yagnik%2C%20the%20One-Man%20Storehouse%20of%20Knowledge%20on%20Gujarat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04121509%2FAchyut-Yagnik.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20mid-1970s%20to%20recent%20times%2C%20if%20anyone%20wanted%20to%20understand%2C%20report%20on%20or%20research%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20mandatory%20first%20stop%20was%20invariably%20Achyut%20Yagnik.%20He%20was%20a%20one-man%20storehouse%20of%20information%2C%20details%2C%20anecdotes%2C%20data%20and%20insight%20about%20the%20political%20landscape%20of%20the%20state%20and%20its%20society%E2%80%99s%20passions%20and%20prejudices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20passed%20away%20early%20this%20morning.%20And%20all%20social%20scientists%20who%20ever%20wrote%20about%20Gujarat%20will%20feel%20a%20personal%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20always%20%E2%80%9CAchyut%20Bhai%E2%80%9D%2C%20always%20available%20for%20a%20spot%20of%20conversation%2C%20or%20a%20dialogue%20if%20you%20preferred%2C%20or%20a%20declamation%20if%20you%20had%20the%20discipline%20of%20patience.%20Either%20way%2C%20it%20was%20always%20a%20rewarding%20encounter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20office%20(SETU%20%E2%80%93%20Centre%20for%20Social%20Knowledge%20and%20Action)%20near%20the%20Commerce%20College%20%3Cem%3Echar-rasta%3C%2Fem%3E%20resembled%20an%20ashram%20in%20its%20bare%20austerity%20but%20suggested%20the%20ambience%20of%20a%20coffee%20house%2C%20where%20over%20many%20cups%20of%20syrupy%20tea%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20smoke%20of%20his%20never-extinguished%20cigarette%20%E2%80%93%20the%20visiting%20interlocutor%20could%20get%20tutored%20into%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20latest%20developments%2C%20be%20it%20the%20Navnirman%20Movement%2C%20the%20anti-reservations%20riots%20of%201981%2C%20the%201985-86%20communal%20flare-up%2C%20the%20anti-Narmada%20dam%20movement%2C%20the%201990-92%20Ayodhya%20violence%2C%20or%20the%20horrible%2C%20horrible%202002%20carnage.%20After%20a%20few%20hours%20with%20him%2C%20the%20reporter%20improved%20his%20copy%2C%20the%20columnist%20enriched%20her%20insight%20and%20the%20researcher%20came%20back%20with%20more%20homework%20to%20do%20before%20the%20dissertation%20could%20be%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20that%20traditional%20pandit%2Fpurohit%20who%20knew%20the%20clan%E2%80%99s%20horoscopes%2C%20Achyut%20Bhai%20was%20the%20original%20%E2%80%98Google%E2%80%99%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20political%20crowd%20of%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%20%E2%80%93%20Sanat%20Mehta%2C%20Jinabhai%20Darji%2C%20Madhavsinh%20Solanki%2C%20Chiman%20Lal%20Patel%2C%20Ashok%20Bhatt%2C%20Keshubhai%20Patel%2C%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%2C%20etc.%20They%20all%20respected%20him%20and%20valued%20his%20views.%20Gujarat%20was%20still%20a%20tolerant%20place%20and%20many%20newspapers%20were%20eager%20to%20publish%20his%20columns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fgujarat-assembly-elections-modi-congress-bjp%5C%22%3EAn%20Interview%20With%20Achyut%20Yagnik%20on%20Distress%20in%20Gujarat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20activists%20like%20Medha%20Patkar%2C%20Bela%20Bhatia%2C%20Madhusudan%20Mistry%20or%20Indukumar%20Jani%2C%20or%20academics%20like%20Dhirubhai%20Seth%2C%20Ashis%20Nandy%2C%20Harsh%20Sethi%2C%20Ghansyam%20Shah%20or%20Anil%20Bhat%2C%20or%20influentials%20like%20Sam%20Pitroda%2C%20Lord%20Bhiku%20Parikh%20or%20Meghnad%20Desai%2C%20or%20researchers%20like%20Shalini%20Randheria%2C%20all%20made%20a%20beeline%20to%20the%20SETU%20office.%20Serving%20and%20retired%20bureaucrats%20often%20dropped%20in%20to%20understand%20or%20clarify%20this%20or%20that%20policy%20initiative%20originating%20from%20Gandhinagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchyut%20Bhai%20was%20an%20odd%20man%20out%20in%20the%20Ahmedabad%20society%2C%20which%20invariably%20judged%20and%20adored%20or%20scorned%20people%20based%20on%20their%20bank%20balance.%20In%20a%20society%20that%20culturally%20prioritised%20wealth%20over%20knowledge%2C%20he%20was%20a%20man%20who%20lived%20on%20his%20own%20terms.%20He%20never%20allowed%20himself%20to%20be%20ensnared%20by%20the%20pretences%20and%20practices%20of%20the%20very%2C%20very%20rich%20Ahmedabadis%20and%20their%20ecosystem%20because%20he%20could%20see%20through%20the%20hypocrisy.%20Against%20the%20entitled%20arrogance%20of%20the%20establishment%2C%20he%20pitted%20the%20clarity%20of%20his%20own%20academic%20solidity%2C%20anchored%20in%20intellectual%20honesty%20and%20personal%20ethics.%20He%20died%20an%20almost%20penniless%20man%2C%20but%20he%20would%20have%20had%20no%20regrets%20because%20he%20also%20lived%20like%20most%20honoured%20among%20the%20honourable%20citizens%20of%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAchyut%20Bhai%20himself%20personified%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20a%20robust%20civil%20society%20%E2%80%93%20keeping%20a%20firm%20distance%20from%20the%20wielders%20of%20power%20in%20Gandhinagar%20yet%20willing%20to%20engage%20with%20%E2%80%9Cauthority%E2%80%9D%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20underprivileged.%20He%20was%20available%20to%20any%20NGO%2C%20any%20movement%2C%20any%20group%20wanting%20to%20correct%20this%20or%20that%20economic%20injustice%20in%20any%20part%20of%20Gujarat.%20Achyut%20Bhai%20would%20often%20direct%20the%20aggrieved%20party%20to%20the%20late%20Girishbhai%20Patel%2C%20the%20intrepid%20lawyer%20who%20fought%2C%20pro%20bono%2C%20interminable%20injustices%20all%20over%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20came%20the%202000s.%20Gujarat%20changed%3B%20new%20economic%20forces%20and%20their%20political%20proxies%20took%20over%20politics%2C%20society%20and%20media.%20The%20new%20Gujarat%20had%20no%20use%20for%20Achyut%20Bhai%E2%80%99s%20views%20or%20ideas%3B%20yet%20he%20remained%2C%20till%20his%20very%20last%2C%20the%20unavoidable%20stop%20for%20anyone%20wanting%20to%20discern%20the%20transformation%20that%20had%20overwhelmed%20all%20the%20good%20men%20and%20women%20of%20Gujarat.%20It%20was%20time%20for%20Achyut%20Bhai%20to%20move%20on%2C%20and%20he%20did%20%E2%80%93%20again%2C%20on%20his%20own%20terms.%20Amen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fhkhare%5C%22%3EHarish%20Khare%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20editor-in-chief%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3EThe%20Tribune%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691131593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04121509%2FAchyut-Yagnik.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fa-salute-to-achyut-yagnik-the-one-man-storehouse-of-knowledge-on-gujarat%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He%20was%20always%20%E2%80%9CAchyut%20Bhai%E2%80%9D%2C%20always%20available%20for%20a%20spot%20of%20conversation%2C%20or%20a%20dialogue%20if%20you%20preferred%2C%20or%20a%20declamation%20if%20you%20had%20the%20discipline%20of%20patience.%20Either%20way%2C%20it%20was%20always%20a%20rewarding%20encounter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A462%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsociety%2Fa-salute-to-achyut-yagnik-the-one-man-storehouse-of-knowledge-on-gujarat%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Violations%20Continue%20in%20J%26K%2C%20Hold%20Assembly%20Elections%20Immediately'%3A%20Report%20on%20Human%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113220%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230756_004.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Five%20years%20since%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20been%20without%20an%20elected%20government%20and%20four%20years%20after%20the%20revocation%20of%20its%20special%20status%20under%20Article%20370%2C%20human%20rights%20violations%20have%20continued%20in%20the%20region%2C%20making%20it%20imperative%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20hold%20assembly%20elections%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Forum%20for%20Human%20Rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20an%20independent%20body%20of%20concerned%20citizens%2C%20released%20its%20fourth%20annual%20report%20on%20Thursday%20titled%20%E2%80%9CFive%20Years%20Without%20an%20Elected%20Administration%3A%20Human%20Rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20August%202022%20%E2%80%93%20July%202023%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20launched%20by%20the%20Forum%20along%20with%20National%20Conference%20president%20Farooq%20Abdullah%2C%20and%20members%20of%20parliament%20Manoj%20Jha%20(RJD)%2C%20Supriya%20Sule%20(NCP)%2C%20Kanimozhi%20(DMK)%2C%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20(Congress)%2C%20Sitaram%20Yechury%20(CPI-M)%20and%20Mohammad%20Yusuf%20Tarigami%20(PAGD).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-chairs%20of%20the%20Forum%20include%20Gopal%20Pillai%2C%20former%20home%20secretary%2C%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20Radha%20Kumar%2C%20former%20member%2C%20Group%20of%20Interlocutors%20for%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20report%20found%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20has%20said%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20counter%20affidavit%20filed%20last%20month%20that%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Act%20of%20August%209%2C%202019%2C%20had%20brought%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9Cunprecedented%20development%2C%20progress%2C%20security%20and%20stability%20to%20the%20region%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20facts%20suggest%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20found%20that%20while%20there%20has%20been%20improvement%20on%20some%20parameters%2C%20human%20rights%20violations%20continue%20on%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20number%20of%20lives%20lost%20due%20to%20armed%20attacks%20and%20counter-insurgency%20operations%20was%20lower%20than%20in%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20the%20number%20of%20police%20personnel%20who%20died%2C%20including%20Central%20Reserve%20Police%20Forces%20(CRPF)%2C%20continues%20to%20be%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C71%20CRPF%20troops%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20four%20years%20between%202019-2022%2C%20twice%20as%20many%20as%20in%20the%20previous%20four%20years%2C%202014-2018%2C%20when%2035%20died.%20By%20comparison%2C%20in%20the%20four%20years%20between%202012-2015%2C%20which%20can%20be%20categorised%20as%20an%20uneasy%20interregnum%20between%20the%20post-peace%20process%20years%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20conflict%20in%20the%20BJP-PDP%20coalition%2C%2027%20CRPF%20troops%20were%20killed%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20also%20drawn%20attention%20to%20the%20resurgence%20of%20militancy%20in%20Jammu%20after%20decades%20of%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%202022%20delimitation%20of%20fresh%20legislative%20constituencies%2C%20adding%20Poonch%20and%20Rajouri%20to%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Anantnag%2C%20may%20have%20added%20to%20the%20alienation%20that%20these%20Muslim-majority%20areas%20face%20with%20the%20sharpening%20of%20communal%20divides%20in%20Jammu%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20improvement%20in%20gross%20violations%20of%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20movement%2C%20especially%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20media%2C%20and%20pointed%20to%20the%20arrests%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20and%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Delhi%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20undertrials%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20its%20prison%20population%20at%2091%25%2C%20against%20the%20national%20average%20of%2076%25%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%E2%80%99s%20prisons%20can%20house%20a%20total%20of%203%2C629%20inmates%2C%20but%20they%20lodged%205%2C300%20as%20of%20June%202023%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20at%2023.1%25%20in%20March%202023%2C%20unemployment%20was%20almost%20three%20times%20the%20national%20average%20of%207.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20while%20a%20record%20year%20of%20tourism%20in%202022%20has%20boosted%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20still%20lags%20behind%20the%20national%20average%20on%20per%20capita%20income%20and%20rates%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeed%20to%20hold%20elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20demand%20of%20the%20report%20is%20to%20highlight%20the%20need%20for%20holding%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20well%20as%20a%20legislative%20assembly%20in%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20nine%20years%20since%20the%20last%20legislative%20election%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20The%20union%20administration%20accepted%20the%20delimitation%20commission%E2%80%99s%20report%20a%20year%20ago%20and%20it%20is%20eight%20months%20since%20fresh%20electoral%20rolls%20were%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20preparations%20for%20an%20election%20have%20thus%20been%20completed%2C%20but%20the%20election%20commission%20has%20yet%20to%20announce%20dates%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20said%20that%20the%20report%20highlights%20the%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20because%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRight%20to%20vote%20and%20periodic%20and%20regular%20elections%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20while%20releasing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHence%20we%20have%20focused%20on%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20other%20big%20concern%20is%20the%20resurgence%20of%20militancy%20in%20Jammu.%20Why%20has%20this%20resurgence%20happened%20after%20decades%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%20said%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20bridge%20the%20trust%20deficit%20that%20exists%20between%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20rulers%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20trust%20deficit%20between%20Delhi%20and%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20If%20this%20nation%20has%20to%20survive%20we%20have%20to%20survive%20together%2C%20we%20cannot%20survive%20by%20dividing%20each%20other%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20report%2C%20Tharoor%20said%20the%20figures%20of%20the%20killing%20of%20CRPF%20jawans%20reflects%20the%20tension%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20persistence%20of%20tension%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20part%20of%20India%20which%20is%20used%20to%20having%20elections%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20had%20polls%20in%20nine%20years.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20initiate%20action%20against%20those%20who%20violate%20human%20rights%20as%20well%20as%20intimidation%20of%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20must%20work%20in%20cooperation%20with%20local%20groups%20to%20ensure%20the%20return%20of%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113203%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230801_002-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666603%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20report%20release%20in%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20Atul%20Ashok%20Howale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJha%20said%20that%20the%20question%20of%20Kashmir%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20whole%20and%20without%20any%20%E2%80%9Cifs%20and%20buts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20immediately.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20difference%20between%20the%20idea%20of%20normalcy%20in%20Delhi%20and%20that%20in%20Kashmir.%20What%20we%20saw%20in%20Manipur%20also%20shows%20that%20the%20idea%20(of%20the%20government)%20is%20to%20use%20polarisation%20and%20majoritarian%20ethos%20to%20win%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESule%20said%20that%20the%20report%20highlights%20the%20failed%20promise%20of%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20who%20had%20promised%20to%20hold%20elections%20a%20year%20after%20revoking%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAmit%20Shah%20had%20promised%20elections%20in%20a%20year%20when%20he%20brought%20the%20bill%20in%20parliament.%20Now%20four%20years%20on%20that%20has%20not%20happened%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYechury%20said%20that%20if%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claims%20are%20to%20be%20believed%2C%20it%20is%20now%20an%20opportune%20moment%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernment%20claims%20peace%20has%20been%20restored%20and%20there%20are%20conditions%20for%20elections.%20If%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%20today%20the%20conditions%20are%20perfect%20to%20hold%20elections%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20militancy%20according%20to%20them%2C%20there%20is%20peace%20and%20tranquility-Then%20why%20are%20elections%20not%20being%20held%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CRestoration%20of%20democratic%20participation%20of%20people%20will%20go%20a%20long%20way.%20Pressure%20must%20be%20mounted%20for%20immediate%20holding%20of%20elections.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20key%20recommendations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20need%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20report%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20government%20should%20accept%20and%20implement%20the%20tribal%20welfare%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20that%20Ladakh%20be%20included%20in%20the%20sixth%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20executive%20authority%20of%20the%20Kargil%20and%20Leh%20hill%20councils%20should%20be%20restored%20and%20the%20prospect%20of%20statehood%20should%20be%20discussed%20with%20concerned%20stakeholders%20in%20Ladakh%20and%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20has%20also%20recommended%20the%20release%20of%20all%20political%20prisoners%20who%20were%20taken%20into%20detention%20on%20or%20after%20August%204%2C%202019%2C%20repeal%20of%20the%20PSA%20and%20other%20preventive%20detention%20legislation%20and%20the%20release%20of%20journalists%20and%20activists%20including%20Irfan%20Mehraj%2C%20Fahad%20Shah%2C%20Aasif%20Sultan%20and%20Khurram%20Pervez%2C%20amongst%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20recommended%20the%20local%20communities%20be%20involved%20in%20facilitating%20the%20return%20of%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%2C%20reinstating%20all%20the%20former%20state%E2%80%99s%20statutory%20oversight%20bodies%2C%20especially%20those%20monitoring%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20there%20is%20also%20a%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20additional%20directorate%20for%20human%20rights%20is%20given%20full%20freedom%20in%20the%20role%20it%20can%20play%20investigating%20alleged%20human%20rights%20abuses%20and%20monitoring%20adherence%20to%20the%20humanitarian%20guidelines%20to%20be%20followed%20when%20conducting%20cordon%20and%20search%20operations%20(CASO)%2C%20to%20prevent%20civilian%20deaths%2C%20injuries%20or%20any%20other%20damage%20or%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20of%20the%20Forum%20include%20Justice%20A.P.%20Shah%2C%20former%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Madras%20and%20Delhi%20high%20courts%2C%20Justice%20Bilal%20Nazki%2C%20former%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Orissa%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20Ruma%20Pal%2C%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%20Justice%20Hasnain%20Masoodi%2C%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20Anjana%20Prakash%2C%20former%20judge%20of%20the%20Patna%20high%20court%2C%20Gopal%20Pillai%2C%20former%20home%20secretary%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20Nirupama%20Rao%2C%20former%20foreign%20secretary%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20Probir%20Sen%2C%20former%20secretary-general%2C%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%2C%20Amitabha%20Pande%2C%20former%20secretary%2C%20Inter-State%20Council%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20Moosa%20Raza%2C%20former%20chief%20secretary%2C%20Government%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Shantha%20Sinha%2C%20former%20chairperson%2C%20National%20Commission%20for%20the%20Protection%20of%20Child%20Rights%2C%20Major-General%20Ashok%20Mehta%20(retd)%2C%20Air%20Vice-Marshal%20Kapil%20Kak%20(retd)%2C%20Lieutenant-General%20H.S.%20Panag%20(retd)%2C%20Colonel%20Yoginder%20Kandhari%20(retd)%2C%20Enakshi%20Ganguly%2C%20co-founder%20and%20former%20co-director%2C%20HAQ%20Centre%20for%20Child%20Rights%2C%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20writer%20and%20historian%2C%20and%20Anand%20Sahay%2C%20columnist.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691129163000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04113220%2Fsignal-2023-08-03-230756_004.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fviolations-continue-in-jk-hold-assembly-elections-immediately-report-on-human-rights%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Forum%20for%20Human%20Rights%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20released%20its%20annual%20report%20on%20Thursday%20in%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fviolations-continue-in-jk-hold-assembly-elections-immediately-report-on-human-rights%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Contentious%20Forest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%202023%20Will%20Soon%20Be%20a%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04111155%2FCentral_India_forest_landscape.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKochi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20a%20move%20that%20will%20have%20huge%20ramifications%20for%20forest%20conservation%20in%20India%2C%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%202%20cleared%20the%20controversial%20Forest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%202023.%20Now%2C%20only%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20Assent%20stands%20between%20the%20Bill%20being%20enacted%20as%20law%20under%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%2C%201980.%20The%20Act%20itself%20will%20have%20a%20new%20name%3A%20the%20Van%20(Sanrakshan%20Evam%20Samvardhan)%20Adhiniyam%2C%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarkedly%20missing%20from%20the%20proceedings%20during%20the%20discussion%20of%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20house%20were%20the%20Members%20of%20Parliament%20of%20opposition%20parties%2C%20who%20had%20walked%20out%20citing%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20statement%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur%2C%20and%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20issue.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20no%20dissent%20was%20tabled%20against%20the%20Bill%20during%20the%20legislative%20process%2C%20though%20some%20members%20raised%20concerns.%20Citizens%20and%20experts%20have%20criticised%20opposition%20leaders%20on%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20has%20been%20controversial%20for%20the%20several%20drastic%20changes%20it%20proposes%20to%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%2C1980%2C%20including%20exempting%20huge%20tracts%20of%20forest%20land%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Act%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20security%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdefence%E2%80%9D%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20controversial%20Bill%20with%20far-reaching%20impacts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2F164.100.47.4%2FBillsTexts%2FLSBillTexts%2FAsintroduced%2F80_2023_LS_ENG329202330923PM.pdf%5C%22%3EForest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20amends%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2005%2Fbill53_2007010153_Handbook_of_Forest_Conservation_Act_1980_and_Forest_Conservation_Rules_2003.pdf%5C%22%3EForest%20Conservation%20Act%20of%201980%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20provides%20for%20the%20conservation%20of%20forests%20across%20the%20country%20in%20several%20ways%20including%20restricting%20the%20use%20of%20forests%20for%20non-forest%20purposes%20(including%20cultivation)%20and%20providing%20for%20the%20constitution%20of%20a%20Forest%20Advisory%20Committee.%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20to%20get%20forest%20clearances%20from%20the%20Committee%20for%20any%20developmental%20activities%20within%20forest%20lands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20proposes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fforest-governance-india-people%2F%5C%22%3Eseveral%20drastic%20changes%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Act%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20promoting%20afforestation%20and%20meeting%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20carbon%20targets.%20The%20Act%20will%20no%20longer%20apply%20to%20some%20forest%20lands%20(such%20as%20deemed%20forests%20and%20community%20forests)%20which%20are%20functional%20forests%20as%20per%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20the%20term%2C%20but%20not%20officially%20recorded%20as%20forests.%20With%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20Act%20will%20apply%20only%20to%20lands%20notified%20as%20a%20forest%20under%20the%20Indian%20Forest%20Act%2C%201927%2C%20or%20those%20that%20have%20been%20officially%20recorded%20as%20a%20forest%20on%20or%20after%20October%2025%2C%201980.%20The%20Bill%2C%20however%2C%20claims%20that%20it%20clarifies%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20scope%20of%20applicability%20of%20the%20Act%20upon%20various%20lands%20so%20as%20to%20remove%20ambiguities%20and%20bring%20clarity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20proposes%20to%20also%20exempt%20forest%20land%20that%20is%20situated%20within%20100%20km%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20or%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20construction%20of%20strategic%20linear%20project%20of%20national%20importance%20and%20concerning%20national%20security%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Act.%20It%20also%20provides%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20zoos%2C%20safaris%20and%20eco-tourism%20facilities%20in%20forest%20areas%20other%20than%20protected%20areas%2C%20which%20was%20not%20specified%20earlier%20in%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20specific%20amendment%20goes%20against%20the%20February%202023%20order%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(which%20it%20gave%20while%20dealing%20with%20alleged%20illegal%20logging%20and%20construction%20in%20tiger%20reserves%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20tiger%20safari%20in%20the%20buffer%20area%20of%20Corbett%20Tiger%20Reserve%20in%20Uttarakhand)%2C%20said%20Sarvadaman%20Oberoi%2C%20a%20legal%20activist%20and%20environmentalist%20from%20Gurgaon.%20In%20this%20order%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20restrained%20construction%20within%20core%20areas%20in%20tiger%20reserves%2C%20national%20parks%20and%20wildlife%20sanctuaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202022%2C%20Haryana%20chief%20minister%20Manohar%20Lal%20Khattar%20announced%20plans%20for%20a%20zoo%20safari%20in%2010%2C000%20acres%20in%20the%20Aravalli%20range%20in%20the%20Gurugram%20and%20Nuh%20districts%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20National%20Capital%20Region.%20Construction%20that%20will%20be%20undertaken%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Aravalli%20safari%20project%20will%20result%20in%20%E2%80%9Ca%20lot%20of%20unnecessary%20real%20estate%20development%20that%20will%20destroy%20the%20native%20ecosystem%20of%20the%20Aravallis%20by%20clearing%20of%20trees%2C%20undergrowth%2C%20vegetation%2C%20grasses%20and%20other%20such%20niche%20habitats%20used%20by%20the%20resident%20wildlife%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Aravalli%20Bachao%20Citizens%20Movement%20said%20in%20the%20suggestions%20it%20submitted%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20regarding%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAllowing%20zoos%20and%20safaris%20within%20the%20scope%20of%20non-forest%20activities%20%5Bas%20the%20Bill%20proposes%20to%20do%5D%20may%20disproportionately%20commercialize%20forests%20and%20wildlife%20without%20due%20consideration%20to%20the%20rights%20of%20forest%20dependent%20people%2C%20wildlife%20and%20ecosystem%20services%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Oberoi.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20cumulative%20impact%20of%20such%20establishments%20including%20buildings%2C%20access%20roads%2C%20power%20transmission%20lines%2C%20vehicular%20movement%2C%20light%20and%20noise%20pollution%20etc%20has%20significant%20impact%20and%20fragments%20an%20otherwise%20intact%20forest%20and%20have%20immense%20impact%20on%20species%20conservation.%20There%20is%20no%20justification%20for%20such%20non-forestry%20activities%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20the%20restrictions%20that%20are%20fundamental%20to%20FCA.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20changes%20brought%20on%20by%20the%20Bill%20will%20impact%20tribal%20communities%20and%20their%20livelihoods%20in%20several%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLoss%20of%20homes%2C%20incomes%2C%20jobs%2C%20and%20socio-ecological%20futures%20are%20certainly%20going%20to%20happen%20with%20the%20repurposing%20of%20these%20lands%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kanchi%20Kohli%2C%20legal%20researcher%20at%20the%20New%20Delhi-based%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%2C%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finterview-why-there-is-mistrust-about-proposed-changes-to-forest-conservation-law%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20April%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2F400-ecologists-write-to-environment-minister-against-amendments-to-forest-conservation-act%5C%22%3Eecologists%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcitizens-climate-action-groups-protest-against-the-passage-of-forest-conservation-amendment-bill%5C%22%3Eactivists%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20conservationists%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmore-than-100-ex-civil-servants-question-new-forest-conservation-amendment-bill%5C%22%3Eretired%20civil%20servants%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20concerned%20citizens%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fobjections-to-proposed-changes-to-forest-conservation-act-pour-in-from-all-corners%2F%5C%22%3Ehad%20raised%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20regarding%20these%20changes.%20Most%20concerns%20submitted%20to%20the%20JPC%2C%20however%2C%20were%20not%20addressed%20in%20the%20report%20tabled%20by%20the%20JPC%20on%20July%2020%20in%20the%20Parliament%3B%20the%20Committee%20%E2%80%93%20which%20received%20more%20than%201%2C300%20submissions%20with%20objections%20and%20recommendations%20to%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdespite-criticism-forest-conservation-amendment-bill-gets-jpc-nod%5C%22%3Ecleared%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20any%20changes%20despite%20inadequate%20justifications%2C%20as%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanges-to-forest-conservation-act-heres-what-an-internal-document-of-the-govt-reveals%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20special%20story.%20On%20July%2026%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20monsoon%20session%20of%20the%20Parliament%2C%20amidst%20protests%20by%20the%20Opposition%20about%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20balance%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20environmental%20progress%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%202%2C%20Union%20environment%20minister%20Bhupender%20Yadav%20presented%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%93%20which%20now%20renames%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%201980%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CVan%20(Sanrakshan%20Evam%20Samvardhan)%20Adhiniyam%2C%201980%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20The%20Forest%20Conservation%20Amendment%20Bill%20is%20being%20introduced%20to%20bring%20changes%20on%20how%20to%20increase%20green%20cover%20along%20with%20balancing%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20environmental%20progress%2C%20Yadav%20said%2C%20while%20presenting%20the%20Bill.%20The%20updated%20Act%20will%20not%20be%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20Tribal%20Rights%20Act%20and%20will%20instead%20strengthen%20tribal%20communities%2C%20he%20insisted.%20If%20people%20in%20tribal%20belts%20need%20some%20land%20for%20government%20facilities%2C%20they%20will%20not%20have%20to%20come%20to%20Delhi%20to%20ask%20for%20it%2C%20development%20will%20go%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20that%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%2C%20he%20added.%20Roads%20and%20land%20in%20areas%20near%20the%20border%20currently%20need%20permission%20for%20clearance.%20India%20also%20has%20to%20develop%20its%20agroforestry%20(including%20medicinal%20plants%20and%20timber)%20which%20this%20Bill%20will%20enable%3B%20it%20will%20help%20tribal%20communities%20by%20permitting%20them%20to%20grow%20such%20trees%2C%20Yadav%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharachchandra%20Lele%2C%20a%20Distinguished%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Ashoka%20Trust%20for%20Research%20in%20the%20Environment%20and%20Ecology%20who%20studies%20aspects%20including%20environmental%20policy%20and%20governance%2C%20termed%20the%20Bill%20as%20%E2%80%9Cgreen-gutting%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fforest-conservation-amendment-bill-2023-positive-environmental-benefits-green-gutting-sc-1996-godavarman-order-8871986%2F%5C%22%3Ecommentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGreenwashing%20refers%20to%20actions%20that%20claim%20to%20provide%20positive%20environmental%20benefits%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20achieve%20much.%20With%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Amendment%20Bill%202023%2C%20the%20government%20is%20going%20one%20step%20further%20and%20indulging%20in%20%E2%80%9Cgreen-gutting%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20using%20pro-environment%20language%20while%20actually%20undermining%20regulations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20opposition%20to%20debate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20opposition%20MPs%20were%20present%20on%20the%20floor%20when%20the%20Bill%20was%20discussed.%20Hence%2C%20no%20dissent%20was%20tabled%20against%20the%20bill%20during%20the%20legislative%20process.%20Many%2C%20including%20experts%20and%20citizens%2C%20expressed%20dismay%20at%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20opportunity%20to%20debate%20the%20Forest%20(Conservation)%20Bill%202023%20arose%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20chose%20to%20boycott%20the%20proceeding%2C%20neglecting%20their%20parliamentary%20responsibility%20and%20showing%20a%20priority%20for%20political%20dominance%20rather%20than%20public%20welfare%E2%80%A6Regrettably%2C%20this%20will%20likely%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20bleakest%20day%20in%20the%20Indian%20environmental%20law%2C%20leaving%20the%20people%20of%20India%20feeling%20profoundly%20betrayed%20by%20the%20opposition%20MPs%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdebadityo%2Fstatus%2F1686697594255503360%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Debadityo%20Sinha%2C%20Senior%20Resident%20Fellow%20and%20Lead%20of%20the%20Climate%20and%20Ecosystems%20team%20at%20the%20Vidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParliamentary%20proceedings%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20law-making%20by%20serving%20as%20the%20primary%20record%20for%20legislative%20intent%20and%20major%20concerns%20related%20to%20a%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdebadityo%2Fstatus%2F1686757788628983814%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20serves%20as%20a%20fundamental%20%E2%80%98reference%20point%E2%80%99%20for%20future%20interpretations%20and%20amendments.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20it%20has%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20shaping%20the%20course%20of%20legislation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ENot%20one%20voice%20stood%20up%20and%20opposed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FConservationOfForestAmendmentBill2023%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23ConservationOfForestAmendmentBill2023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Not%20one%20person%20stood%20up%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20forests%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20Not%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20stakeholders%20of%20our%20children%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20the%20protectors%20of%20our%20well-being%2C%20our%20elected%20representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FZzPcGAqrwE%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FZzPcGAqrwE%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Dia%20Mirza%20(%40deespeak)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdeespeak%2Fstatus%2F1686935985144401920%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20extremely%20disheartening%20to%20see%20the%20government%20go%20ahead%20with%20this%20ecologically%20destructive%20bill%20despite%20receiving%20so%20many%20letters%20and%20emails%20from%20conservationists%2C%20ecologists%2C%20ex%20civil%20servants%2C%20tribal%2C%20forest%20and%20citizen%20groups%20from%20across%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20Neelam%20Ahluwalia%2C%20Founder%20Member%20of%20the%20Aravalli%20Bachao%20Citizens%20Movement%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CUrban%20and%20rural%20citizens%20are%20extremely%20disappointed%20and%20feel%20a%20huge%20sense%20of%20betrayal%20from%20the%20members%20of%20parliament%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties%20who%20instead%20of%20opposing%20this%20regressive%20bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chose%20to%20boycott%20the%20parliament.%20They%20have%20failed%20in%20their%20duty%20as%20our%20elected%20leaders%20to%20protect%20India%E2%80%99s%20forests%2C%20biodiversity%2C%20wildlife%2C%20air%20quality%2C%20water%20security%2C%20rights%20of%20tribal%20communities%20and%20the%20future%20of%20our%20youth%20in%20this%20time%20of%20extreme%20climate%20crisis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20they%20supported%20the%20Bill%20overall%2C%20some%20members%20%E2%80%93%20including%20V.%20Vijaysai%20Reddy%20of%20YSRCP%20and%20G.K.%20Vasan%20of%20the%20Tamil%20Maanila%20Congress%20(Moopanar)%20%E2%80%93%20raised%20concerns%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%202.%20The%20Sikkim%20Democratic%20Front%E2%80%99s%20Hishey%20Lachungpa%20said%20that%20public%20utility%20lands%20have%20been%20crucial%20for%20the%20tribal%20population%20of%20Sikkim%20and%20many%20of%20these%20people%20live%20along%20the%20borders%20of%20the%20country.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20new%20amendment%20should%20be%20inclusive%20of%20providing%20forest%20rights%20of%20these%20Sikkimese%20tribal%20populations%20which%20in%20no%20way%20will%20cause%20deforestation%20%5Bbut%5D%20maintain%20ecological%20balance%20and%20strengthen%20our%20border%20civilian%20population%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Regarding%20defence%20infrastructure%20along%20border%20areas%2C%20sacred%20lakes%20and%20pilgrimage%20sites%20should%20be%20avoided%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CApprehensions%20are%20arising%20that%20biodiversity%20may%20be%20affected%20in%20pursuit%20of%20the%20new%20forest%20amendment%20act%E2%80%A6biodiversity%20and%20natural%20treasures%20should%20be%20safeguarded%20and%20protected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiju%20Janata%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20Prashant%20Nanda%20from%20Odisha%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20dilution%20of%20protection%20of%20deemed%20forest%20areas%20and%20if%20the%20new%20changes%20would%20affect%20the%20categories%20of%20land%20notified%20as%20forest%20land%20or%20waiting%20to%20be%20notified.%20He%20also%20noted%20that%20compensatory%20afforestation%20conducted%20in%20another%20place%20does%20not%20offer%20the%20same%20ecosystem%20services%20such%20as%20water%20and%20clean%20air%20as%20the%20natural%20forest%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fforests%2Frajya-sabha-passes-forest-conservation-amendment-bill-amid-confusion-concerns-90967%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDTE%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Collective%20decision%20to%20boycott%E2%80%99%3A%20Jairam%20Ramesh%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20tweet%20on%20August%203%2C%20Jairam%20Ramesh%2C%20former%20Union%20environment%20minister%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20main%20opposition%20party%2C%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20%E2%80%9Cclarified%E2%80%9D%20the%20Opposition%E2%80%99s%20stand%20on%20the%20issue%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20decision%20to%20boycott%20was%20a%20collevtive%20%5Bsic%5D%20decision%20of%2026%20INDIA%20parties%20because%20our%20legitimate%20demand%20for%20a%20statement%20by%20PM%20on%20Manipur%20followed%20by%20a%20discussion%20is%20being%20refused%20daily%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20is%20simply%20not%20allowed%20to%20speak%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ramesh%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20against%20standard%20procedure%2C%20the%20Bill%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20and%20not%20the%20usual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fparliamentary-committees%2Fscience-technology-environment-forests%5C%22%3EStanding%20Parliamentary%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20Environment%20and%20Forests)%2C%20currently%20headed%20by%20former%20environment%20minister%20and%20Congress%20leader%20Jairam%20Ramesh.%20Ramesh%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjairam-ramesh-protests-as-bill-to-amend-forest-act-not-sent-to-parliamentary-standing-committee%5C%22%3Eobjected%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20this.%20He%20reiterated%20this%20in%20his%20tweet%20too%2C%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20was%20a%20complete%20mockery%20of%20the%20legislative%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20spoken%20repeatedly%20against%20the%20amendments%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tweeted.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20it%20should%20not%20be%20forgotten%20that%20the%20battles%20we%20are%20fighting%20are%20across%20a%20very%20wide%20political%20canvas.%20At%20times%2C%20a%20legitimate%20and%20principled%20stand%20on%20a%20larger%20issue%20can%20have%20consequences%20on%20a%20specific%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CQuestions%20should%20be%20asked%20of%20this%20government%20and%20even%20other%20parties%20that%20played%20ball%20and%20rubber-stamped%20this%20insidious%20Bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20be%20a%20long%20struggle%20for%20the%20environment%20and%20securing%20the%20rights%20of%20adivasis%20and%20forest%20dwellers%2C%20and%20there%20should%20be%20no%20doubt%20where%20the%20Opposition%20stands%20on%20this%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1686707792940261376%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%202%2C%20Ramesh%20had%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cboth%20the%20substance%20of%20the%20amendments%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Cbulldozed%20through%20in%20Parliament%20reflect%20the%20mindset%20of%20the%20Modi%20Government%2C%20and%20the%20vast%20gap%20that%20exists%20between%20its%20global%20talk%20and%20domestic%20walk%20on%20the%20environment%2C%20forests%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20adivasis%20and%20other%20forest-dwelling%20communities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20clearing%20of%20the%20Bill%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%202%2C%20all%20that%20now%20stands%20in%20the%20way%20of%20the%20Bill%20being%20enacted%20as%20law%20under%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%2C%201980%2C%20is%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20Assent.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691127772000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F04111155%2FCentral_India_forest_landscape.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcontentious-forest-conservation-amendment-bill-2023-will-soon-be-a-law%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Rajya%20Sabha%20cleared%20the%20Bill%20on%20August%202%3B%20no%20dissent%20was%20tabled%20against%20the%20controversial%20bill%20because%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20walked%20out%20of%20Parliament%20protesting%20the%20lack%20of%20discussion%20on%20the%20Manipur%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcontentious-forest-conservation-amendment-bill-2023-will-soon-be-a-law%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IndiGo%20flight%20makes%20emergency%20landing%20in%20Patna%20due%20to%20engine%20trouble%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691127749000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-02%2F11%2Ffull%2F1581417166-7137.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Findigo-flight-makes-emergency-landing-in-patna-due-to-engine-trouble-123080400173_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Indigo%20flight%20on%20Patna%20Delhi%20route%20returned%20to%20its%20origin%20due%20to%20a%20technical%20issue.%20Three%20minutes%20after%20its%20dep